<P align=left><IMG src="ms3206591-def14a1x2x1.jpg" border=0></P>
<TABLE style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid" width="30%"></TD>
    <TD style="BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid" width="70%">
      <P align=right><IMG src="ms3206591-def14a1x2x2.jpg" border=0><BR><FONT face=Arial size=2 color=#007BC4>James P. Gorman<br>&nbsp;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid" width="30%" bgColor=#ffffff>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: #007bc4 1pt solid; width: 70%; padding-bottom: 4pt"><BR>
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>April 7, 2017</FONT></P>
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Dear fellow shareholders,</FONT></P>
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>I cordially invite you to attend
      Morgan Stanley&#146;s 2017 annual meeting of shareholders that will be held on
      Monday, May 22, 2017, at our offices at 2000 Westchester Avenue, Purchase,
      New York. I hope that you will be able to attend, and, if not, I encourage
      you to vote by proxy. Your vote is very important.</FONT></P>
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>2016 demonstrated that we have the
      right business mix, risk profile, and size and scale to drive Morgan
      Stanley&#146;s future success through market cycles. Our financial performance
      improved over the previous year, as we grew our pre-tax profit, excluding
      DVA</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2 color=#007BC4>*</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>, by
      nearly $1 billion despite nearly flat revenues. Our return on equity,
      excluding DVA</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2 color=#007BC4>*</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>, demonstrated progress towards our 2017 target, but we need to
      continue to execute on our strategic initiatives this year to get there.
      While there is more work to be done to achieve our goals, we approach 2017
      with more confidence than at any time over the past 10 years.</FONT></P>
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>We took further steps in 2016 to
      develop the next generation of leadership, cross-pollinating key
      executives throughout our major businesses to create a greater focus on
      collaboration and delivering the entire Firm for the benefit of our
      clients.</FONT></P>

<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>In addition to the ongoing dialogue we maintain with
      shareholders, we sought to engage with a number of you over the past year
      to hear your perspectives on governance, compensation and environmental
      and social issues. Based on the insights you shared, we have enhanced our
      disclosures to better communicate our best-in-class practices, including
      with respect to Board oversight, director orientation and education, our
      director equity ownership requirement, our commitment to delivering
      compensation that is well aligned with performance, and our management
      succession and development planning. The Board continues to focus on
      succession, adding nine new directors in the past five years with
      complementary skills and attributes to focus on overseeing a sustainable,
      long-term strategy. At your request, we have also added disclosure
      reflecting our sustainability efforts and giving back to the communities
      in which we serve.</FONT></P>
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>As we do each year, the Board of
      Directors and executive management have evaluated our strategy and refined
      our goals and priorities to ensure we are working for the long-term
      benefit of our shareholders.</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P align=right><FONT face=Arial color=#b3b5b8 size=2>Morgan Stanley 2017 Proxy
Statement</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT><FONT face=Arial color=#007bc4 size=2>1</FONT></P>
<HR align=center width="100%" noShade SIZE=2>

<DIV style="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE: always"></DIV><BR>
<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=2><A href="#toc">Table of Contents</A></FONT></B></P>
<TABLE style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="BORDER-TOP: #007bc4 1pt solid; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid" width="30%" bgColor=#ffffff>&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-top: #007bc4 1pt solid; border-bottom: #007bc4 1pt solid; width: 70%; padding-top: 4pt; padding-bottom: 4pt">
      <DIV style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Our Wealth Management business is poised for further
      growth, and we are focused on increasing our pre-tax earnings. In 2016 our
      full-year profit margin</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2 color=#007BC4>*</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2> was 22%, despite headwinds from muted retail
      investor engagement and sustained low interest rates. Assuming
      constructive markets, we have targeted a profit margin of 23% to 25% by
      2017.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Our world-class Investment Banking franchise continued
      to rank in the top two of the global league tables in advising on mergers
      and acquisitions and underwriting initial public offerings last
      year.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>We unified our Sales &amp; Trading franchise under one
      leadership team in the fall of 2015, and now are managing Sales &amp;
      Trading holistically, aiming to optimize resources, talent, capital and
      technology. Our Equity Sales &amp; Trading business finished the year No.
      1 globally in net revenues for the third year in a row. Our goal is to
      maintain leadership across regions while profitably growing wallet share.
      The meaningful restructuring of our Fixed Income Sales &amp; Trading
      business made at the end of 2015 was consistent with our objective to have
      a credible and critically sized business with capital and resources
      appropriate to the market opportunities. The results so far have been
      encouraging, and in 2016 we exceeded our goal of average quarterly net
      revenues of at least $1 billion.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>In Investment Management, we undertook an organizational
      realignment to unify the business, rationalize costs and take better
      advantage of the Firm&#146;s distribution and origination platforms. While we
      experienced lower revenue from investments in 2016, our management fees
      were stable and we demonstrated strong momentum in fundraising across a
      number of funds, launched new products, and strengthened the management
      team.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>On the expense side, we remain vigilant and are on
      course to deliver our targeted $1 billion of cost reductions in 2017
      through Project Streamline. On relatively flat annual net revenues in
      2016, we reduced non-compensation expenses significantly and also
      continued to exercise discipline on compensation expenses.</FONT></DIV>
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>We increased both our common
      dividend and share repurchase program last year. Our total capital return
      in 2016 was $4.8 billion, an increase of 50% from the prior year. We
      believe we are sufficiently capitalized for our business mix, size and
      risk profile.</FONT></P>
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>More details on our strategy and
      growth opportunities across the businesses are detailed in my Letter to
      Shareholders. I hope you will read this letter, which also includes
      details on our efforts to develop the next generation of leadership. I
      have great confidence in this team, and we are well positioned for the
      years ahead.</FONT></P>
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Thank you for your support of Morgan Stanley.</FONT></P>
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Very truly yours,</FONT></P>
      <P align=left><IMG src="ms3206591-def14a1x3x1.jpg" border=0></P>
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>James P. Gorman <BR></FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Chairman and Chief Executive Officer</FONT></I></P>
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=1 color=#007BC4><SUP>* </SUP></FONT><FONT face=Arial size=1>Represents a non-GAAP measure. See page 57 for the &#147;Notes to the
      Compensation Discussion and Analysis.&#148;</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE><BR>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial color=#007bc4 size=2>2</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT><FONT face=Arial color=#b3b5b8 size=2>Morgan Stanley 2017 Proxy Statement</FONT></P>

certain information that you should consider before voting on the items

proxy statement carefully before voting. In this proxy statement, we refer to
Morgan Stanley as the &#147;Company,&#148; the &#147;Firm,&#148; &#147;we,&#148; &#147;our&#148; or &#147;us&#148; and the Board
of Directors as the &#147;Board.&#148;</FONT></P>

    <TD NOWRAP STYLE="vertical-align: middle; text-align: center; width: 1%; background-color: #e6e7e8; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt"></TD>
    <TD NOWRAP STYLE="vertical-align: middle; text-align: center; width: 14%; background-color: #007bc4; padding: 2pt 6pt">
      <P align=center><B><FONT color=#ffffff><FONT face=Arial size=1>Sustainability<BR>and
      Social<BR>Responsibility</FONT></FONT></B></P></TD>
    <TD NOWRAP STYLE="vertical-align: middle; text-align: center; width: 1%; background-color: #e6e7e8; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt"></TD>
    <TD STYLE="border: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: middle; text-align: left; width: 83%; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt">
      <DIV style="PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; FONT-SIZE: 7.5pt; TEXT-INDENT: -13pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 7pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=1><FONT face=Arial size=1>Established the Morgan Stanley
      Institute for Sustainable Investing and committed to facilitating the
      financing of sustainable and social impact projects</FONT></FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; FONT-SIZE: 7.5pt; TEXT-INDENT: -13pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 7pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=1><FONT face=Arial size=1>Company-wide focus on managing
      our environmental footprint</FONT></FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; FONT-SIZE: 7.5pt; TEXT-INDENT: -13pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 7pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=1><FONT face=Arial size=1>Commitment to giving back to the

<TABLE style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 2pt; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid" noWrap align=left width="100%" bgColor=#ffffff><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt" face=Arial color=#007bc4>2016 CEO Performance and Compensation
      Decision</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>At the start of 2016, as in prior years,
the CMDS Committee established a target range of CEO compensation ($10 million
to $28 million) and the factors to be considered in determining year-end
compensation.</FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>At year end, 2016 CEO compensation was set
at $22.5 million, a 7% increase from $21 million for 2015, with
shareholder-aligned features: 72% deferred over three years and subject to
clawback, with 39% of such deferred compensation delivered through future
performance-vested equity awards.</FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The 2016 pay decision for the CEO was
based on the CMDS Committee&#146;s assessment of Mr. Gorman&#146;s strong individual
performance and Morgan Stanley&#146;s progress in relation to its strategic
objectives, financial performance and shareholder returns.</FONT></P>

      <P align=center><B><FONT face=Arial size=1>5-Year (2012-2016)

  <TR STYLE="background-color: rgb(233,234,238)">
    <TD NOWRAP STYLE="width: 33%; text-align: center; padding-right: 6pt; padding-left: 6pt">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD NOWRAP STYLE="width: 1%; text-align: center; padding-right: 6pt; padding-left: 6pt">&nbsp;</TD>

  <TR Valign=bottom STYLE="background-color: rgb(233,234,238)">
    <TD NOWRAP STYLE="width: 33%; text-align: center; padding-bottom: 2pt; padding-right: 6pt; padding-left: 6pt"><IMG src="ms3206591-def14a2x3x2.jpg" border=0></TD>
    <TD NOWRAP STYLE="width: 1%; text-align: center; padding-bottom: 2pt; padding-right: 6pt; padding-left: 6pt"></TD>

<P align=right><FONT face=Arial size=2 color=#b3b5b8>Morgan Stanley 2017 Proxy Statement</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2><FONT color=#007bc4>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;9</FONT></FONT></P>

<DIV style="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE: always"></DIV><BR>
<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=2><A href="#toc">Table of Contents</A></FONT></B></p>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=1><FONT color=#b3b5b8>OVERVIEW OF VOTING
ITEMS</FONT></FONT></P>
<DIV style="BORDER-RIGHT: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; PADDING-RIGHT: 15pt; BORDER-TOP: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; BORDER-LEFT: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; BORDER-BOTTOM: #b3b5b8 1pt solid"><BR>
<TABLE style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 2pt; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid" noWrap align=left width="100%" bgColor=#ffffff><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt" face=Arial color=#007bc4>2016 CEO Compensation
  Elements</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>CEO compensation was delivered in a
combination of base salary, cash bonus, deferred cash, restricted stock units
(RSUs) and a long-term incentive program (LTIP) award in the form of performance
stock units, as outlined in the chart below. A significant portion of CEO pay is
deferred, awarded in equity, subject to future stock price performance,
cancellation and clawback and, in the case of the LTIP award, subject to future
achievement of specified financial goals over a three-year period.</FONT></P>
<TABLE style="LINE-HEIGHT: normal; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

      Elements</FONT></B></TD>

program include:</FONT></P>

  <TR vAlign=bottom>

      cover material adverse outcomes, even absent misconduct</FONT></FONT></TD>
    <TD NOWRAP STYLE="border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; text-align: left; width: 1%; padding-right: 6pt; padding-left: 6pt"><FONT size=3 face="Times New Roman"><FONT face=Arial color=#007cc3>&#10003;</FONT><FONT></FONT></FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR vAlign=bottom>

      requirements</FONT></FONT></TD>

      compensation programs</FONT></FONT></TD>

<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2><FONT color=#007bc4>10&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2 color=#b3b5b8>Morgan Stanley 2017 Proxy Statement</FONT></P>

<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=2><A href="#toc">Table of Contents</A></FONT></B></p>
<P align=right><FONT face=Arial size=1><FONT color=#b3b5b8>OVERVIEW OF VOTING
ITEMS</FONT></FONT></P>
<DIV style="BORDER-RIGHT: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; PADDING-RIGHT: 15pt; BORDER-TOP: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; BORDER-LEFT: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; PADDING-TOP: 10pt; BORDER-BOTTOM: #b3b5b8 1pt solid">
<TABLE style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 2pt; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid" noWrap align=left width="100%" bgColor=#ffffff><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt" face=Arial color=#007bc4>Shareholder
Engagement</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>At our 2016 annual meeting of
shareholders, approximately 90% of the votes cast were in favor of our annual
&#147;Say on Pay&#148; proposal. In anticipation of the 2017 &#147;Say on Pay&#148; vote, we
continued our engagement program, seeking feedback from shareholders and proxy
advisory firms on a variety of topics, including executive compensation,
corporate governance and environmental and social goals. With respect to executive
compensation, shareholders who provided feedback during our engagement program
generally reported that executive compensation at Morgan Stanley was viewed as
well-aligned with performance.</FONT></P></DIV><BR>
<TABLE cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=4 width="10%" border=0>

  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD style="TEXT-ALIGN: center" noWrap width="99%" bgColor=#007bc4><B><FONT face=Arial><FONT color=#ffffff>Item
4</FONT></FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE>
<DIV style="BORDER-RIGHT: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; PADDING-RIGHT: 15pt; BORDER-TOP: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; BORDER-LEFT: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; BORDER-BOTTOM: #b3b5b8 1pt solid" align=center><BR>
<DIV style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 6pt" align=left><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt" face=Arial color=#007bc4>Company Proposal to Vote on the Frequency of Holding a
Non-Binding Advisory Vote on the Compensation of Executives as Disclosed in the
Proxy Statement (Non-Binding Advisory Vote)</FONT></B></DIV>
<TABLE cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 2pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top; WIDTH: 1%"><IMG src="ms3206591-def14a2x2x1.jpg" border=0></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial style="font-size: 11pt">Our Board unanimously recommends
      that you vote for the option of once every <FONT color=#007bc4>&#147;1
      YEAR&#148;</FONT> as the frequency with which shareholders are provided a
      non-binding advisory vote on executive
  compensation.</FONT></B></P></TD></TR></TABLE><BR>
<DIV style="PADDING-RIGHT: 15pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #e6e7e8" align=center><BR>
<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=1 color=#007bc4>Proposal</FONT></B></P>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 7.5pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; BORDER-TOP: #007bc4 1pt solid; PADDING-LEFT: 4pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top; BORDER-LEFT: #007bc4 1pt solid; PADDING-TOP: 4pt; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #ffffff" vAlign=top WIDTH=1%><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 7.5pt" color=#007bc4 >&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="BORDER-RIGHT: #007bc4 1pt solid; BORDER-TOP: #007bc4 1pt solid; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top; PADDING-TOP: 4pt; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #ffffff" vAlign=top WIDTH=99%>
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>An annual &#147;Say on Pay&#148;
      vote</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE><BR>
<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=1 color=#007bc4>Rationale</FONT></B></P>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="padding: 4pt 8pt 5pt 4pt; border-top: #007bc4 1pt solid; border-left: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; background-color: #ffffff; width: 1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 5pt; border-right: #007bc4 1pt solid; border-top: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; padding-top: 4pt; background-color: #ffffff; width: 99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>In 2011, the Firm&#146;s shareholders
      indicated their preference for holding the &#147;Say on Pay&#148; vote on an annual
      basis, with 91% of votes cast in support</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 5pt; padding-right: 8pt; padding-left: 4pt; border-left: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 1%; background-color: #ffffff"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD COLSPAN="2" STYLE="padding-bottom: 5pt; border-right: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 99%; background-color: #ffffff">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>While the Firm&#146;s executive
      compensation program is designed to promote a long-term connection between
      pay and performance, an annual vote allows shareholders to provide their
      view on our compensation philosophy, policies and practices each
      year</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; PADDING-LEFT: 4pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top; BORDER-LEFT: #007bc4 1pt solid; WIDTH: 1%; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #ffffff" width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="BORDER-RIGHT: #007bc4 1pt solid; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top; WIDTH: 99%; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #ffffff" width="99%" colSpan=2>
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>An annual &#147;Say on Pay&#148; vote is
      consistent with the Firm&#146;s practice of seeking the views of, and engaging
      in discussions with, shareholders on governance and compensation
      matters</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE><BR></DIV><BR>
<TABLE>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 2pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top; WIDTH: 1%"><IMG src="ms3206591-def14a2x2x2.jpg" border=0></TD>
    <TD style="WIDTH: 99%; TEXT-ALIGN: left">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=1>See page 74 for the proposal to vote
      on the frequency of holding a non-binding advisory vote on the
      compensation of executives as disclosed in the proxy statement
      (non-binding advisory vote).</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE><BR></DIV><BR>

<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=1 color=#007bc4>Proposal</FONT></B></P>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="padding: 4pt 8pt 5pt 4pt; border-top: #007bc4 1pt solid; border-left: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; background-color: #ffffff; vertical-align: top; width: 1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 5pt; border-right: #007bc4 1pt solid; border-top: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; padding-top: 4pt; background-color: #ffffff; vertical-align: top; width: 99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Add 50 million shares to the
      EICP</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 5pt; padding-right: 8pt; padding-left: 4pt; border-left: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 1%; background-color: #ffffff"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD COLSPAN="2" STYLE="padding-bottom: 5pt; border-right: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 99%; background-color: #ffffff">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Extend the term of the EICP for an
      additional 5 years</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; PADDING-LEFT: 4pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt; BORDER-LEFT: #007bc4 1pt solid; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid" vAlign=top width="1%" bgColor=#ffffff><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>

      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Re-approve, for purposes of Section
      162(m) of the Internal Revenue Code, the performance criteria set forth in
      the plan</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE><BR>
<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=1 color=#007bc4>Rationale</FONT></B></P>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="padding: 4pt 10pt 5pt 4pt; border-top: #007bc4 1pt solid; border-left: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; background-color: #ffffff; width: 1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 5pt; border-right: #007bc4 1pt solid; border-top: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; padding-top: 4pt; background-color: #ffffff; width: 99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Morgan Stanley believes that a
      portion of compensation should be awarded in shares to align employee and
      shareholder interests</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 5pt; padding-right: 8pt; padding-left: 4pt; border-left: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 1%; background-color: #ffffff"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD COLSPAN="2" STYLE="padding-bottom: 5pt; border-right: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 99%; background-color: #ffffff">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Company last amended the EICP in
      2016 to add 20 million shares, which was approved by approximately 94% of
      the votes cast</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 5pt; padding-right: 8pt; padding-left: 4pt; border-left: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 1%; background-color: #ffffff"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD COLSPAN="2" STYLE="padding-bottom: 5pt; border-right: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 99%; background-color: #ffffff">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Company is requesting an
      additional 50 million shares in 2017, which we expect would allow us to
      make grants under the EICP for approximately three years</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 5pt; padding-right: 8pt; padding-left: 4pt; border-left: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 1%; background-color: #ffffff"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD COLSPAN="2" STYLE="padding-bottom: 5pt; border-right: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 99%; background-color: #ffffff">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Company strives to maximize
      employee and shareholder alignment, while minimizing dilution. The share
      repurchase program offsets the dilutive impact of these additional
      shares</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR STYLE="background-color: White">
    <TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 5pt; padding-right: 8pt; padding-left: 20pt; border-left: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9675;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 5pt; border-right: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 99%">Since
      Morgan Stanley re-initiated the share repurchase program in 2013, the
      Company has increased share repurchases each year - 12 million, 28
      million, 59 million, and 117 million shares from 2013 to 2016,
    respectively</TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; PADDING-LEFT: 4pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top; BORDER-LEFT: #007bc4 1pt solid; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #ffffff"  WIDTH=1%><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="BORDER-RIGHT: #007bc4 1pt solid; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #ffffff"  WIDTH=99%>
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Re-approval of the plan performance
      criteria will better enable performance-vested awards to be tax-deductible
      to Morgan Stanley under Section 162(m) of the Internal Revenue Code, which
      Morgan Stanley believes to be in the best interests of the Company and our
      shareholders</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE><BR>

    <TD STYLE="width: 100%; padding-top: 2pt; text-align: left"><FONT face=Arial size=1>Overhang represents the number of
      shares underlying outstanding employee equity awards and available for
      future employee equity awards as a percentage of weighted average common
      shares outstanding for the period.</FONT></TD></TR>

    <TD STYLE="width: 100%; padding-top: 2pt; text-align: left"><FONT face=Arial size=1>Burn rate represents the number of

      of weighted average common shares outstanding for the
  period.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE></div><BR>

<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=1 color=#007bc4>Proposal</FONT></B></P>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; BORDER-TOP: #007bc4 1pt solid; PADDING-LEFT: 4pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top; BORDER-LEFT: #007bc4 1pt solid; PADDING-TOP: 4pt; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #ffffff" vAlign=top  WIDTH=1%><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="BORDER-RIGHT: #007bc4 1pt solid; BORDER-TOP: #007bc4 1pt solid; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top; PADDING-TOP: 4pt; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #ffffff" vAlign=top  WIDTH=99%>
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Add 1 million shares to
      DECAP</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE><BR>
<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=1 color=#007bc4>Rationale</FONT></B></P>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 7.5pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="padding: 4pt 8pt 5pt 4pt; border-top: #007bc4 1pt solid; border-left: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; background-color: #ffffff; width: 1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 5pt; border-right: #007bc4 1pt solid; border-top: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 99%; padding-top: 4pt; background-color: #ffffff; width: 99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Approval will preserve the Firm&#146;s
      ability to grant stock units to non-employee directors</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 5pt; padding-right: 8pt; padding-left: 4pt; border-left: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 1%; background-color: #ffffff"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD COLSPAN="2" STYLE="padding-bottom: 5pt; border-right: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 99%; background-color: #ffffff">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Morgan Stanley believes stock unit
      grants promote the Firm&#146;s long-term interests by attracting, motivating
      and retaining qualified non-employee directors and more closely align their interests with those of
    shareholders</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="padding-bottom: 5pt; padding-right: 8pt; padding-left: 4pt; border-left: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 1%; background-color: #ffffff"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD COLSPAN="2" STYLE="padding-bottom: 5pt; border-right: #007bc4 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 99%; background-color: #ffffff">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Non-employee directors receive a
      vast majority of their compensation in the form of stock units, half of
      which are not payable until retirement</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; PADDING-LEFT: 4pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top; BORDER-LEFT: #007bc4 1pt solid; WIDTH: 1%; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #ffffff" width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="BORDER-RIGHT: #007bc4 1pt solid; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top; WIDTH: 99%; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #ffffff" width="99%" colSpan=2>
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>In 2016, DECAP was amended to
      include an aggregate limit of $750,000 on annual non-employee director
      compensation and we introduced a non-employee director equity ownership
      requirement of 5x the annual cash
retainer</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE><BR></DIV><BR>
<TABLE>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 2pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top; WIDTH: 1%"><IMG src="ms3206591-def14a2x2x2.jpg" border=0></TD>

    <TD style="BORDER-RIGHT: #b3b5b8 1pt solid" vAlign=top>&nbsp;</TD></TR>

      that you vote</FONT></B> <B><FONT face=Arial size=2 color=#007bc4>&#147;AGAINST&#148;</FONT></B>
      <B><FONT face=Arial size=2>each shareholder proposal.</FONT></B></P></TD>
    <TD style="BORDER-RIGHT: #b3b5b8 1pt solid" vAlign=top>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="BORDER-LEFT: #b3b5b8 1pt solid">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>

    <TD vAlign=top width="99%" bgColor=#ffffff>&nbsp;</TD>

  <TR>
    <TD style="BORDER-LEFT: #b3b5b8 1pt solid">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD width="99%" colSpan=2>
      <DIV style="padding-bottom: 4pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -13pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Our Board recommends you vote against the proposal to
      exclude votes to abstain from shareholder proposal vote
      counts.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -13pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Our Board recommends you vote against the proposal to
      adopt a policy to prohibit vesting of deferred equity awards for senior
      executives who resign to enter government service.</FONT></DIV></TD>
    <TD style="BORDER-RIGHT: #b3b5b8 1pt solid" vAlign=top bgColor=#ffffff>&nbsp;</TD></TR>

    <TD vAlign=top width="99%" bgColor=#ffffff></TD>

<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial style="font-size: 22pt"><FONT color=#007bc4><A NAME="p14"></A>CORPORATE

  <TR vAlign=bottom>

<TABLE cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="BORDER-TOP: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; BORDER-LEFT: #b3b5b8 1pt solid">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD style="BORDER-TOP: #b3b5b8 1pt solid" width="99%" colSpan=2>&nbsp;</TD>

    <TD width="99%" colSpan=2>
      <P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial color=#007bc4>Election of
      Directors</FONT></B></P></TD>
    <TD style="BORDER-RIGHT: #b3b5b8 1pt solid" vAlign=top>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="BORDER-LEFT: #b3b5b8 1pt solid">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%"></TD>
    <TD style="BORDER-RIGHT: #b3b5b8 1pt solid" vAlign=top>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="BORDER-LEFT: #b3b5b8 1pt solid">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 2pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top; WIDTH: 1%"><IMG src="ms3206591-def14a2x2x1.jpg" border=0></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial style="font-size: 11pt">Our Board unanimously recommends
      that you vote</FONT></B> <B><FONT face=Arial color=#007bc4 size=2>&#147;FOR&#148;</FONT></B> <B><FONT face=Arial size=2>the election of all
      director nominees.</FONT></B></P></TD>
    <TD style="BORDER-RIGHT: #b3b5b8 1pt solid" vAlign=top>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="BORDER-LEFT: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; BORDER-BOTTOM: #b3b5b8 1pt solid">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 2pt; VERTICAL-ALIGN: top; WIDTH: 1%; BORDER-BOTTOM: #b3b5b8 1pt solid">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD style="BORDER-BOTTOM: #b3b5b8 1pt solid" vAlign=top width="99%">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD style="BORDER-RIGHT: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; BORDER-BOTTOM: #b3b5b8 1pt solid" vAlign=top>&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE>
<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial style="font-size: 14pt" color=#007bc4><A NAME="p14-2"></A>DIRECTOR SELECTION AND NOMINATION
PROCESS</FONT></B></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Our Board currently consists of 15
directors, including two directors who are designated in accordance with the
terms of the Investor Agreement between Morgan Stanley and Mitsubishi UFJ
Financial Group, Inc. (MUFG), dated October 13, 2008, as amended and restated
(Investor Agreement), pursuant to which Morgan Stanley agreed to take all lawful
action to cause two of MUFG&#146;s senior officers or directors to become members of
Morgan Stanley&#146;s Board. MUFG has designated Messrs. Nobuyuki Hirano and Ryosuke
Tamakoshi as its representative directors pursuant to the Investor
Agreement.</FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Nominating and Governance Committee&#146;s
charter provides that the committee will actively seek and identify nominees for
recommendation to the Board consistent with the criteria in the Morgan Stanley
Corporate Governance Policies (Corporate Governance Policies), which provide
that the Board values members who:</FONT></P>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="padding-right: 8pt; padding-left: 15pt; vertical-align: top; width: 1%; padding-bottom: 4pt"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; width: 99%; padding-bottom: 4pt">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2></FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Combine a broad spectrum of experience and expertise with a
      reputation for integrity;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="padding-right: 8pt; padding-left: 15pt; vertical-align: top; width: 1%; padding-bottom: 4pt"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; width: 99%; padding-bottom: 4pt">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Have experience in positions with a
      high degree of responsibility;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="padding-right: 8pt; padding-left: 15pt; vertical-align: top; width: 1%; padding-bottom: 4pt"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; width: 99%; padding-bottom: 4pt">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Are leaders in the companies or
      institutions with which they are affiliated;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="padding-right: 8pt; padding-left: 15pt; vertical-align: top; width: 1%; padding-bottom: 4pt"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; width: 99%; padding-bottom: 4pt">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Can make contributions to the Board
      and management; and</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Represent the interests of
      shareholders.</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>While the Board has not adopted a policy
regarding diversity, the Corporate Governance Policies provide that the Board
will take into account the diversity of a director candidate&#146;s perspectives,
background and other relevant demographics. The Nominating and Governance
Committee and Board may also determine specific skills and experience they are
seeking in director candidates based on the needs of the Company at a specific
time. In considering candidates for the Board, the Nominating and Governance
Committee considers the entirety of each candidate&#146;s credentials in the context
of these criteria.</FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Board is committed to the ongoing
review of Board composition and director succession planning. Nine new
directors, who bring a diversity of skills, backgrounds, experience, attributes
and perspectives to the Board, have joined the Board since 2012. The Nominating
and Governance Committee continuously reviews the experience, qualifications,
attributes, skills and tenure of the members of the Board and maintains a list
of potential director candidates that is reviewed and refreshed throughout the
course of the year.</FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Nominating and Governance Committee
may also consider director candidates proposed by shareholders, and in this
regard, the Board has adopted the Policy Regarding Director Candidates
Recommended by Shareholders. The Nominating and Governance Committee may also
retain and terminate, in its sole discretion, a third party to assist in
identifying director candidates or gathering information regarding a director
candidate&#146;s background and experience. Members of the Nominating and Governance
Committee, the Independent Lead Director and other members of the Board
interview potential director candidates as part of the selection process when
evaluating new director candidates.</FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2><FONT color=#007bc4>14&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT></FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2 color=#b3b5b8>Morgan Stanley 2017 Proxy Statement</FONT></P>
<HR align=center width="100%" noShade SIZE=2>


<!--PART 03-->
<DIV style="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE: always"></DIV><BR>
<P align=left><A href="#toc"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Table of
Contents</FONT></B></A></P>
<P align=right><FONT face=Arial color=#b3b5b8 size=1>CORPORATE
GOVERNANCE</FONT></P>
<P align=left><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 14pt" face=Arial color=#007bc4><A NAME="p15"></A>DIRECTOR
EXPERIENCE, QUALIFICATIONS, ATTRIBUTES AND SKILLS</FONT></B></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>When the Board nominates directors for
election at an annual meeting, it evaluates the experience, qualifications,
attributes and skills that an individual director candidate contributes to the
tapestry of the Board as a whole to assist the Board in discharging its duties
and overseeing the Company&#146;s strategy. As part of the ongoing process to
evaluate these attributes, the Board performs an annual self-evaluation and the
Corporate Governance Policies provide that the Board expects a director to
advise the Chairman and Corporate Secretary if he or she plans to join the board
of directors or similar governing body of another public or private company or
advisory board, or experiences other changed circumstances that could diminish
his or her effectiveness as a director or otherwise be detrimental to the
Company, and to advise and to offer to tender his or her resignation for
consideration by the Board if his or her principal occupation or employer
changes. In addition, the Corporate Governance Policies provide that a director
candidate should not be nominated for election if the candidate would be 72
years old at the time of election.</FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Company believes that an effective
board consists of a diverse group of individuals who bring a variety of
complementary skills and a range of tenures. The Nominating and Governance
Committee and Board regularly consider these skills in the broader context of
the Board&#146;s overall composition, with a view toward constituting a board that
has the best skill set and experience to oversee the Company&#146;s business and to
ensure that the Board has the appropriate mix of skills needed for the broad set
of challenges that it confronts. Our directors have a combined wealth of
leadership experience derived from extensive service guiding large, complex
organizations as executive leaders or board members and in government and
academia and possess substantive knowledge and skills applicable to our
business, including experience in the following areas:</FONT></P>
<P align=left><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 12pt" face=Arial color=#007bc4>Directors&#146; Qualifications, Attributes and Skills</FONT></B></P>

    <TD NOWRAP STYLE="text-align: left; width: 20%; background-color: #e6ebf8; padding-bottom: 6pt; padding-right: 6pt"></TD></TR></TABLE><BR>
<P align=left><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 14pt" face=Arial color=#007bc4><A NAME="p15-1"></A>DIRECTOR
NOMINEES</FONT></B></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Board stands for election at each
annual meeting of shareholders. Each director holds office until his or her
successor has been duly elected and qualified or the director&#146;s earlier
resignation, death or removal.</FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Board has nominated the 14 director
nominees below for election at the 2017 annual meeting of shareholders. The
Board believes that, in totality, the mix of qualifications and the diversity of
skills, attributes and perspectives among the nominees enhances our Board&#146;s
effectiveness in light of the Company&#146;s businesses, regulatory environment and
long-term strategy.</FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>In accordance with the Board&#146;s retirement
policy, Donald T. Nicolaisen is not standing for re-election at the annual
meeting of shareholders. The Board thanks Mr. Nicolaisen for his dedicated
service to Morgan Stanley.</FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>As part of the Board&#146;s ongoing review of
Board composition and succession planning, the Nominating and Governance
Committee&#146;s third-party search firm recommended Dennis M. Nally as a potential
director candidate to the Nominating and Governance Committee. Upon the
recommendation of the Nominating and Governance Committee, the Board unanimously
elected Mr. Nally to the Board, effective October 1, 2016. The Board determined
that Mr. Nally&#146;s service as former Chairman of PricewaterhouseCoopers
International Ltd. brings to the Board extensive regulatory, public accounting
and financial reporting experience as well as technology and management
experience.</FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Each nominee has indicated that he or she
will serve if elected. We do not anticipate that any nominee will be unable or
unwilling to stand for election, but if that happens, your proxy may be voted
for another person nominated by the Board or the Board may reduce the number of
directors to be elected.</FONT></P>
<P align=right><FONT face=Arial color=#b3b5b8 size=2>Morgan Stanley 2017 Proxy
Statement&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT><FONT color=#007bc4 size=2 face=arial>15</FONT></P>

  <TR>
    <TD vAlign=top width="49%" colSpan=3>
      <DIV style="padding-bottom: 2pt;PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007BC4>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>President Emeritus of the University of North Carolina
      and served as President from January 2006 through December
      2010.</FONT></DIV>

      <DIV style="padding-bottom: 2pt;PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007BC4>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Served as Co-Chair of the National Commission on Fiscal
      Responsibility and Reform during 2010.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="padding-bottom: 2pt;PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007BC4>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Senior advisor at BDT Capital Partners LLC, a private
      investment firm, since 2012 and serves as non-executive vice chairman.
      Senior advisor from 2001 to 2015 and Managing Director from 1999 to 2001
      of Carousel Capital, a private investment firm. Partner at the private
      investment firm of Forstmann Little &amp; Co. from 1999 to 2001 and a
      founder of Kitty Hawk Capital, a venture capital firm.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="padding-bottom: 2pt;PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007BC4>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Began career in corporate finance at Morgan Stanley in
      1969 and subsequently helped found and served as Chairman and CEO of
      Bowles Hollowell Connor &amp; Co., an investment banking
      firm.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007BC4>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Served as White House Chief of Staff from 1996 to 1998
      and Deputy White House Chief of Staff from 1994 to 1995. Head of the Small
      Business Administration from 1993 to 1994 and served as United Nations
      Under Secretary General, Deputy Special Envoy for Tsunami Recovery in
      2005.</FONT></DIV><BR>
      <DIV style="PADDING-RIGHT: 6pt; PADDING-LEFT: 6pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 6pt; PADDING-TOP: 6pt; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #E6EBF8" align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2><FONT color=#007BC4>Qualifications,
      Attributes and Skills:</FONT> Mr. Bowles brings to the Board his extensive
      experience in the financial services industry and our Company,
      particularly in his capacity as Independent Lead Director appointed by our
      independent directors, as well as in academia and his distinguished public
      service.</FONT></DIV>
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2><FONT color=#007BC4>Other Current
      Public Company Directorships:</FONT><BR>Facebook, Inc. and Norfolk
      Southern Corporation</FONT></P>
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2><FONT color=#007BC4>Other Public
      Company Directorships in the Past Five Years:</FONT><BR>Belk, Inc. and
      Cousins Properties Incorporated</FONT></P></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="1%"></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="49%" colSpan=3>
      <DIV style="padding-bottom: 4pt;PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007BC4>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Appointed to the House of Lords on December 10, 2015.
      Previously a member of the British Parliament, serving as a member of the
      House of Commons from 1987 to 2015.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007BC4>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Held several leadership positions, including as
      Chancellor of the Exchequer from 2007 to 2010, Secretary of State for
      Trade and Industry from 2006 to 2007, Secretary of State for Scotland from
      2003 to 2006, Secretary of State for Transport from 2002 to 2006,
      Secretary of State for Social Security/Work and Pensions from 1998 to 2002
      and Chief Secretary to the Treasury from 1997 to 1998.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007BC4></FONT>&nbsp;</DIV><BR>
      <DIV style="PADDING-RIGHT: 6pt; PADDING-LEFT: 6pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 6pt; PADDING-TOP: 6pt; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #E6EBF8" align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2><FONT color=#007BC4>Qualifications,
      Attributes and Skills:</FONT> Mr. Darling&#146;s service as a former member of
      the British Parliament and as Chancellor of the Exchequer brings to the
      Board strong leadership, risk management and regulatory experience, as
      well as insight into both the global economy and the global financial
      system.</FONT></DIV></TD></TR>

      roles, including as Chairman of the Financial Accounting Standards
      Board.</FONT></DIV>
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial color=#007BC4 size=2>Other Current Public
      Company Directorships:<BR></FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Federal National
      Mortgage Association (Fannie Mae) and Workiva Inc.</FONT></P></TD>

      MUFG, one of the world&#146;s leading financial groups, since April 2013, and
      since April 2016 Chairman of The Bank of Tokyo-Mitsubishi UFJ, Ltd.
      (BTMU), the core commercial banking unit of MUFG.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="padding-bottom: 4pt;PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" face=arial color=#007BC4>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Director of MUFG since June

      <DIV style="padding-bottom: 4pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" face=arial color=#007BC4>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Numerous senior-level

<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=2><A href="#toc">Table of Contents</A></FONT></B></p>
<P STYLE="text-align: right"><FONT face=Arial color=#b3b5b8 size=1>CORPORATE
GOVERNANCE</FONT></P>
<P align=left><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 14pt" face=Arial color=#007bc4><A NAME="p23"></A>CORPORATE GOVERNANCE HIGHLIGHTS</FONT></B></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Morgan Stanley is committed to
best-in-class governance practices which are embodied in our Corporate
Governance Policies available at www.morganstanley.com/about-us-governance. The
Board initially adopted the Corporate Governance Policies in 1995 and reviews
and approves them annually to ensure they reflect evolving best practices and
regulatory requirements, including the New York Stock Exchange (NYSE) corporate
governance listing standards. The governance practices highlighted below are
reflected in the Corporate Governance Policies, bylaws and our committee
charters, as applicable.</FONT></P>
<TABLE style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 2pt; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid" noWrap align=left width="100%" bgColor=#ffffff><B><FONT face=Arial color=#007bc4 style="font-size: 11pt"><A NAME="p23-1"></A>Board Structure and
Independence</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Our Board
      represents a tapestry of complementary skills, attributes and perspectives
      and includes individuals with financial services experience and a diverse
      international background.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Directors may not
      stand for election if they would be 72 years old at the time of
    election.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Our Board conducts
      an ongoing review of Board composition and succession planning, resulting
      in nine new directors since 2012 who bring a diversity of skills,
      attributes and perspectives to the Board.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Upon election at
      the annual meeting, the average tenure of the members of the Board will be
      approximately 4.9 years.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Our Board has a
      majority of independent directors. Our Chairman is the only member of
      management who serves as a director.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Our Independent
      Lead Director is selected from and by the independent directors and has
      expansive duties set forth in our Corporate Governance Policies. The
      Independent Lead Director chairs regularly scheduled executive sessions
      without the Chairman present. See &#147;Board Leadership Structure and Role in
      Risk Oversight.&#148;</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">The Independent
      Lead Director and committee chairs serve for approximately 3-5 years to
      provide for rotation of Board leadership and committee chairs while
      maintaining experienced leadership.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">In accordance with
      the Board&#146;s policy regarding the periodic rotation of committee
      appointments in order to facilitate the rotation of committee chairs while
      preserving experienced leadership, the Board has approved the following
      committee appointments since the beginning of 2015:</TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 25pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9675;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Messrs. Nally and
      Traquina were appointed as members of the <B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Audit
      Committee</FONT></B><FONT face=Arial size=2>;</FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 25pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9675;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Messrs. Kleinfeld
      and Owens were appointed as members and Ms. Olayan was appointed Chair of
      the <B><FONT face=Arial size=2>CMDS Committee</FONT></B><FONT face=Arial size=2>;</FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 25pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9675;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Messrs. Bowles and Herz were
      appointed as members of the </FONT><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Nominating
      and Governance Committee</FONT></B><FONT face=Arial size=2>;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 25pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9675;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Ms. Miscik was appointed a member of
      the </FONT><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Operations and Technology
      Committee</FONT></B><FONT face=Arial size=2>; and</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 25pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9675;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%">Mr. Darling and Ms.
      Miscik were appointed as members and Mr. Traquina was appointed as a
      member and Chair of the <B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Risk
      Committee</FONT></B><FONT face=Arial size=2>.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><br>

<TABLE style=" BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 2pt; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid" noWrap align=left width="100%" bgColor=#ffffff><B><FONT face=Arial color=#007bc4 style="font-size: 11pt"><A NAME="p23-2"></A>Board Oversight</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><br>

<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">The Board oversees
      the Company&#146;s strategy and annual business
plans.</TD></TR></TABLE>

<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN:left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 25pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9675;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%"><FONT face=Arial size=2>Conducts an annual strategy offsite with the CEO, Operating
      Committee and senior management to review the Company&#146;s long-term
      strategy.</FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 25pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9675;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Receives regular
      reporting regarding strategy at Board meetings as well as by the CEO and
      Operating Committee outside of regularly scheduled meetings.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 25pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9675;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Reviews the
      Company&#146;s annual strategic presentation to shareholders, which summarizes
      the Company&#146;s progress on the prior year&#146;s strategic plan, provides an
      overview of long-term strategic priorities and includes specific financial
      and non-financial goals. The Company&#146;s 2017 strategic presentation is
      available at
http://www.morganstanley.com/about-us-ir.</TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%">The Board oversees
      the Company&#146;s practices and procedures relating to culture, values and
      conduct.</TD></TR></TABLE>
<P align=right><FONT face=Arial size=2 color=#B3B5B8>Morgan Stanley 2017 Proxy
Statement&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2 color=#007BC4>23</FONT></P>
<HR align=center width="100%" noShade SIZE=2>

<DIV style="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE: always"></DIV><BR>
<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=2><A href="#toc">Table of Contents</A></FONT></B></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial color=#b3b5b8 size=1>CORPORATE
GOVERNANCE</FONT></P>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">The Board oversees
      the Company&#146;s global ERM framework and is responsible for helping to
      ensure that the Company&#146;s risks are managed in a sound manner. The Board
      regularly reviews the Company&#146;s risks and the responsibilities of
      management and the Board committees to assist the Board in its risk
      oversight. See &#147;Board Leadership Structure and Role in Risk
  Oversight.&#148;</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">The Board has a
      separate committee responsible for Operations and Technology, including
      cybersecurity risk, and the Board receives annual briefings on
      cybersecurity, including an assessment from an external party.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Non-employee
      directors meet regularly with our primary regulator, the Federal Reserve,
      and other global regulators as requested.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Directors have
      complete and open access to senior members of management and other
      employees of the Company.</TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 25pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9675;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Board members meet
      with local management and independent control functions throughout the
      world and have visited several of our global offices.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 25pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9675;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">The Independent
      Lead Director and committee chairs meet with management between regularly
      scheduled meetings for discussion of key items and to develop Board and
      committee agendas and provide feedback regarding information reported to
      the Board and on other topics to be reviewed.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 25pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9675;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">The Company&#146;s Chief
      Financial Officer (CFO), Chief Legal Officer (CLO) and Chief Risk Officer
      (CRO), as well as the heads of the Company&#146;s operating units and other
      officers, regularly attend Board meetings and maintain an ongoing dialogue
      with Board members between Board meetings.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 25pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9675;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The CMDS Committee, in conjunction
      with the entire Board, annually reviews succession plans for the CEO and
      senior executives.</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">The director equity
      ownership requirement helps to align director and shareholder interests
      and was enhanced in 2016 with the adoption of a requirement to hold shares
      and equity awards with a value equal to five times the annual Board cash
      retainer. Directors also may not enter into hedging transactions in
      respect of Morgan Stanley common stock or pledge Morgan Stanley common
      stock in connection with a margin or other loan transaction.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%">The Board, the Independent Lead Director and
      each committee have the right at any time to retain independent financial,
      legal or other advisors at the Company&#146;s expense.</TD></TR></TABLE><BR>
<TABLE style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 2pt; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid" noWrap align=left width="100%" bgColor=#ffffff><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt" face=Arial color=#007bc4><A NAME="p24"></A>Annual Evaluation of Board, Committees and
      Independent Lead Director</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">The Board conducts
      an annual evaluation of the performance and effectiveness of the Board,
      the Independent Lead Director and each of its standing committees.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">The annual
      evaluation includes self-evaluations by each of these committees and the
      Board and an evaluation of the performance of the Independent Lead
      Director by the other independent directors led by the chair of the
      Nominating and Governance Committee.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">This process
      includes one-on-one Board member interviews led by the Independent Lead
      Director or committee chair, as appropriate, written guidelines that are
      updated annually to reflect significant new developments or such other
      means as the Nominating and Governance Committee determines appropriate,
      and may encompass such factors as duties and responsibilities, individual
      director performance, Board and committee membership and structure,
      culture, process, agenda topics, presentation materials and
  execution.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%">The Nominating and Governance Committee ensures
      that the results of such evaluations, including any suggestions to enhance
      the performance and effectiveness of the Independent Lead Director, the
      Board and its committees, are communicated to and discussed with the
      entire Board in executive session, the Independent Lead Director and each
      committee, as appropriate. Following such evaluation, Board policies and
      practices are revised as appropriate.</TD></TR></TABLE>
<P></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial color=#007bc4 size=2>24&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
</FONT><FONT face=Arial color=#b3b5b8 size=2>Morgan Stanley 2017 Proxy
Statement</FONT></P>
