Contents</A></FONT></B></P>
<P STYLE="text-align: right"><FONT face=Arial color=#b3b5b8 size=1>CORPORATE
GOVERNANCE</FONT></P>
<TABLE style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 2pt; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid" noWrap align=left width="100%" bgColor=#ffffff><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt" face=Arial color=#007bc4><A NAME="p25"></A>Director Orientation and Continuing
      Education</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Director education
      about Morgan Stanley, our strategy, control framework, regulatory
      environment and our industry begins when a director is elected to our
      Board and continues throughout his/her tenure on the Board.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">We also provide an
      orientation program for new directors, which includes an overview of
      director duties and our corporate governance policies as well as
      presentations by senior management, including the President, the CFO, CLO
      and CRO on the Company&#146;s strategy and regulatory framework, its primary
      business lines and control framework, as well as a one-on-one session with
      the Chairman and CEO.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">As directors are
      appointed to new committees or assume a leadership role, such as committee
      chair, they receive additional orientation sessions specific to such
      responsibilities.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%">We also conduct
      educational briefings on business, governance, regulatory and control
      matters, and reimburse directors for reasonable costs incurred attending
      educational sessions on subjects that would assist them in discharging
      their duties.</TD></TR></TABLE>
<br>
<TABLE style=" BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 2pt; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid" noWrap align=left width="100%" bgColor=#ffffff><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt" face=Arial color=#007bc4><A NAME="p25-1"></A>Senior Management Succession and Development
      Planning</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">The CMDS Committee
      oversees CEO and senior management succession and development planning,
      which covers unexpected as well as planned events and is formally
      reviewed, in conjunction with the entire Board, at least annually.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Our CEO and our
      Chief Human Resources Officer review recommendations and evaluations of
      potential internal CEO and senior management successors, and review their
      qualifications, skills, accomplishments and developmental areas.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%">Potential internal
      CEO and senior management successors regularly attend Board meetings and
      engage with Board members periodically between Board meetings, including
      during preparatory meetings, client-related events and visits to our
      offices around the world. These interactions provide the Board with the
      knowledge of the Company&#146;s executive talent that is critical to the
      Company&#146;s succession planning.</TD></TR></TABLE>
<br>
<TABLE style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 2pt; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid" noWrap align=left width="100%" bgColor=#ffffff><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt" face=Arial color=#007bc4><A NAME="p25-2"></A>Shareholder Rights and
    Accountability</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">All directors are
      elected annually.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">In uncontested
      director elections, directors are elected by a majority of votes
  cast.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Proxy access
      permits up to 20 shareholders owning 3% or more of our stock continuously
      for at least three years to nominate the greater of two directors or up to
      20% of our Board and include those nominees in our proxy materials.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Our Board has an
      Independent Lead Director with expansive duties. See &#147;Board Leadership
      Structure and Role in Risk Oversight&#151;Independent Lead Director.&#148;</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Shareholders who
      own at least 25% of common stock have the ability to call a special
      meeting of shareholders.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">There are no
      supermajority vote requirements in our charter or bylaws.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">We do not have a
      &#147;poison pill&#148; in effect.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Shareholders and
      other interested parties may contact any of our Company&#146;s directors.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%">Shareholders may
      submit recommendations for director candidates for consideration by the
      Nominating and Governance Committee at any time by sending the information
      set forth in the Policy Regarding Director Candidates Recommended by
      Shareholders to the Nominating and Governance Committee, Morgan Stanley,
      Suite D, 1585 Broadway, New York, New York 10036. Under the policy, the
      Nominating and Governance Committee evaluates director candidates
      recommended by shareholders in the same manner as other director
      candidates. In order for director candidate recommendations to be
      considered for the 2018 annual meeting of shareholders, recommendations
      must be submitted in accordance with the policy by December 8,
  2017.</TD></TR></TABLE>
<br>
<TABLE style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 2pt; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid" noWrap align=left width="100%" bgColor=#ffffff><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt" face=Arial color=#007bc4><A NAME="p25-3"></A>Shareholder
Engagement</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Our Board and management value the views
      of our shareholders and engage with them year-round on a broad range of
      topics, including our strategy, financial performance, executive
      compensation, governance practices and our environmental and social
      initiatives.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">We also speak with proxy advisors to
      discuss, and receive feedback on, our executive compensation
  programs.</TD></TR>
    <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD  vAlign=top width="99%">In recent years, the Board has taken action responsive to such shareholder feedback, including the adoption of
amendments to our bylaws to implement proxy access.
</TD></TR>
  </TABLE>

Statement&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2 color=#007BC4>25</FONT></P>

<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=2><A href="#toc">Table of Contents</A></FONT></B></P>
<P STYLE="text-align: right"><FONT face=Arial size=1 color=#B3B5B8>CORPORATE GOVERNANCE</FONT></P>

<TABLE style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 2pt; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid" noWrap align=left width="100%" bgColor=#ffffff><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt" face=Arial color=#007bc4><A NAME="p27"></A>Corporate Political Activities Policy
      Statement</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Over the last several years, the Board has
enhanced its Corporate Political Activities Policy Statement to ensure
transparency of the Company&#146;s practices and procedures regarding political
activities and oversight by senior management and the Board. Our Corporate
Political Activities Policy Statement:</FONT></P>
<P align=left>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="padding-right: 5pt; padding-left: 15pt; padding-bottom: 4pt; vertical-align: top; width: 1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Prohibits Morgan
      Stanley from making U.S. political contributions.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="padding-right: 5pt; padding-left: 15pt; padding-bottom: 4pt; vertical-align: top; width: 1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Provides that
      Morgan Stanley informs its principal U.S. trade associations not to use
      payments made by Morgan Stanley for election-related activity at the
      federal, state or local levels.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="padding-right: 5pt; padding-left: 15pt; padding-bottom: 4pt; vertical-align: top; width: 1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Provides that
      principal U.S. trade association memberships and expenditures relating to
      such memberships are reviewed annually with the Government Relations
      Department and the Nominating and Governance Committee.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="padding-right: 5pt; padding-left: 15pt; padding-bottom: 4pt; vertical-align: top; width: 1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Provides a link to
      examples of principal U.S. trade associations that the Company belongs to
      on the Company&#146;s website.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="padding-right: 5pt; padding-left: 15pt; padding-bottom: 4pt; vertical-align: top; width: 1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Addresses oversight
      of lobbying activities by a member of the Operating Committee of the
      Company who reports to the Chairman and CEO, and significant lobbying
      priorities by the Nominating and Governance Committee.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="padding-right: 5pt; padding-left: 15pt; padding-bottom: 4pt; vertical-align: top; width: 1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Provides that the
      Nominating and Governance Committee oversees the Corporate Political
      Activities Policy Statement and the activities addressed by
  it.</TD></TR></TABLE></P>
<TABLE style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 2pt; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid" noWrap align=left width="100%" bgColor=#ffffff><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt" face=Arial color=#007bc4><A NAME="p27-1"></A>Communication by Shareholders and Other
      Interested Parties with the Board of
Directors</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE><BR>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Shareholders and
      other interested parties may contact any of our Company&#146;s directors
      (including the Independent Lead Director or non-management directors) by
      writing to them at Morgan Stanley, Suite D, 1585 Broadway, New York, New
      York 10036.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Such communications
      will be handled in accordance with the procedures approved by the
      Company&#146;s independent directors.</TD></TR></TABLE><BR>
<TABLE style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 2pt; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid" noWrap align=left width="100%" bgColor=#ffffff><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt" face=Arial color=#007bc4><A NAME="p27-2"></A>Additional Corporate Governance Information
      Available on Corporate Governance Webpage</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE>

Policies and other policies described above, our governance webpage includes the

<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=2><A href="#toc">Table of Contents</A></FONT></B></p>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial color=#b3b5b8 size=1>CORPORATE
GOVERNANCE</FONT></P>
<TABLE style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 2pt; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid" noWrap align=left width="100%" bgColor=#ffffff><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt" face=Arial color=#007bc4><A NAME="p28"></A>Director
Independence</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Board has adopted Director
Independence Standards, which are more stringent than the independence
requirements outlined in the NYSE rules in certain respects, and delineate
relationships that are deemed to impair independence and categories of
relationships that are not deemed material for purposes of director independence
(Director Independence Standards). The Director Independence Standards, which
are part of our Corporate Governance Policies available at
www.morganstanley.com/about-us-governance, provide that for a director to be
considered independent, a director must meet the following categorical
standards:</FONT></P>
<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt">1. Employment and commercial
relationships affecting independence</FONT></B></P>

<TABLE cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="border-top: #007bc4 1pt solid; border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 15%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt; padding-left: 4pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2 color=#007BC4>A. Current
      Relationships</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-top: #007bc4 1pt solid; border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 1%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-top: #007bc4 1pt solid; border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 83%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt; padding-right: 4pt">
      <P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=2></FONT></B><FONT face=Arial size=2>A director will not be independent if: <BR></FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>(i) the director is a current partner or current employee of Morgan
      Stanley&#146;s internal or external auditor; <BR></FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>(ii) an immediate family member of the director is a current
      partner of Morgan Stanley&#146;s internal or external auditor;<BR>(iii) an
      immediate family member of the director (a) is a current employee of
      Morgan Stanley&#146;s internal or external auditor and (b) personally works on
      Morgan Stanley&#146;s audit;<BR>(iv) the director is a current employee, or an
      immediate family member of the director is a current executive officer, of
      an entity that has made payments to, or received payments from, Morgan
      Stanley for property or services in an amount which, in any of the last
      three fiscal years, exceeds the greater of $1 million or 2% of such other
      company&#146;s consolidated gross revenues; or<BR>(v) the director&#146;s spouse,
      parent, sibling or child is currently employed by Morgan
      Stanley.</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 15%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt; padding-left: 4pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2 color=#007BC4>B. Relationships<BR>
within Preceding<BR>

      Three Years</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 1%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 83%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt; padding-right: 4pt">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>A director will not be independent
      if, within the preceding three years:<BR>(i) the director is or was an
      employee of Morgan Stanley; <BR></FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>(ii) an
      immediate family member of the director is or was an executive officer of
      Morgan Stanley;<BR>(iii) the director or an immediate family member of the
      director (a) was a partner or employee of Morgan Stanley&#146;s internal or
      external auditor and (b) personally worked on Morgan Stanley&#146;s audit
      within that time;<BR>(iv) the director or an immediate family member of
      the director received more than $120,000 in direct compensation in any
      12-month period from Morgan Stanley, other than (a) director and committee
      fees and pension or other forms of deferred compensation for prior service
      (provided such compensation is not contingent in any way on continued
      service) and (b) compensation paid to an immediate family member of the
      director who is an employee (other than an executive officer) of Morgan
      Stanley; or<BR>(v) a present Morgan Stanley executive officer is or was on
      the compensation committee of the board of directors of a company that
      concurrently employed the Morgan Stanley director or an immediate family
      member of the director as an executive
officer.</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2 color=#007BC4>28&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2 color=#b3b5b8>Morgan Stanley 2017 Proxy Statement</FONT></P>
<HR align=center width="100%" noShade SIZE=2>

<DIV style="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE: always"></DIV><BR>
<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=2><A href="#toc">Table of Contents</A></FONT></B></P>
<P STYLE="text-align: right"><FONT face=Arial size=1 color=#b3b5b8>CORPORATE GOVERNANCE</FONT></P>
<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt">2. Relationships not deemed material
for purposes of director independence</FONT></B></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>In addition to the provisions above, each
of which must be fully satisfied with respect to each independent director, the
Board must affirmatively determine that the director has no material
relationship with Morgan Stanley. To assist the Board in this determination, it
has adopted the following categorical standards of relationships that are not
considered material for purposes of determining a director&#146;s independence. Any
determination of independence for a director that does not meet these
categorical standards will be based upon all relevant facts and circumstances
and the Board shall disclose the basis for such determination in the Company&#146;s
proxy statement.</FONT></P>

<TABLE cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="border-top: #007bc4 1pt solid; border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 15%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt; padding-left: 4pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2 color=#007BC4>A. Equity
      Ownership</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-top: #007bc4 1pt solid; border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 1%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-top: #007bc4 1pt solid; border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 83%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt; padding-right: 4pt">
      <P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=2></FONT></B><FONT face=Arial size=2>A relationship arising solely from a director&#146;s ownership of an
      equity or limited partnership interest in a party that engages in a
      transaction with Morgan Stanley, so long as such director&#146;s ownership
      interest does not exceed 5% of the total equity or partnership interests
      in that other party.</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 15%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt; padding-left: 4pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2 color=#007BC4>B. Other Directorships</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 1%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 83%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt; padding-right: 4pt">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>A relationship arising solely from a
      director&#146;s position as <BR><FONT face=Arial size=2>(i) director or
      advisory director (or similar position) of another company or for-profit
      corporation or organization or<BR>(ii) director or trustee (or similar
      position) of a tax-exempt organization.</FONT></FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 15%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt; padding-left: 4pt"><FONT size=2 face="Arial" color=#007BC4>C. Ordinary Course<BR>
Business</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 1%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 83%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt; padding-right: 4pt"><FONT size=2 face="Arial">A relationship arising solely
      from transactions, including financial services transactions such as
      underwriting, banking, lending or trading in securities, commodities or
      derivatives, or from other transactions for products or services, between
      Morgan Stanley and a company of which a director is an executive officer,
      employee or owner of 5% or more of the equity of that company, if such
      transactions are made in the ordinary course of business and on terms and
      conditions and under circumstances (including, if applicable, credit or
      underwriting standards) that are substantially similar to those prevailing
      at the time for comparable transactions, products or services for or with
      unaffiliated third parties.</FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 15%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt; padding-left: 4pt"><FONT size=2 face="Arial" color=#007BC4>D. Contributions</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 1%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 83%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt; padding-right: 4pt"><FONT size=2 face="Arial">A relationship arising solely
      from a director&#146;s status as an executive officer of a tax-exempt
      organization, and the contributions by Morgan Stanley (directly or through
      the Morgan Stanley Foundation or any similar organization established by
      Morgan Stanley) to the organization are less than the greater of
      $1,000,000 or 2% of the organization&#146;s consolidated gross revenues during
      the organization&#146;s preceding fiscal year (matching of employee charitable
      contributions is not included in Morgan Stanley&#146;s contributions for this
      purpose).</FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 15%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt; padding-left: 4pt"><FONT size=2 face="Arial" color=#007BC4>E. Products and
    Services</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 1%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 83%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt; padding-right: 4pt"><FONT size=2 face="Arial">A relationship arising solely
      from a director utilizing products or services of Morgan Stanley in the
      ordinary course of business and on substantially the same terms as those
      prevailing at the time for comparable products or services provided to
      unaffiliated third parties.</FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 15%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt; padding-left: 4pt"><FONT size=2 face="Arial" color=#007BC4>F. Professional,<BR>
Social and
      Religious<BR>
Organizations<BR>
and Educational<BR>
Institutions</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 1%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 83%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt; padding-right: 4pt"><FONT size=2 face="Arial">A relationship arising solely
      from a director&#146;s membership in the same professional, social, fraternal
      or religious association or organization, or attendance at the same
      educational institution, as an executive officer or director.</FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 15%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt; padding-left: 4pt"><FONT size=2 face="Arial" color=#007BC4>G. Family Members</FONT></TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 1%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD STYLE="border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 83%; background-color: #ffffff; padding-top: 2pt; padding-bottom: 2pt; padding-right: 4pt"><FONT size=2 face="Arial">Any relationship or transaction
      between an immediate family member of a director and Morgan Stanley shall
      not be deemed a material relationship or transaction that would cause the
      director not to be independent if the standards in this Section 2 would
      permit the relationship or transaction to occur between the director and
      Morgan Stanley.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Board has determined that 11 of our 14
director nominees (Messrs. Bowles, Darling, Glocer, Herz and Kleinfeld, Ms.
Miscik, Mr. Nally, Ms. Olayan, and Messrs. Owens, Traquina and Wilkins) are
independent in accordance with the Director Independence Standards. The Board
has also determined that Dr. Tyson, who retired from the Board during 2016, was
independent during the time she served on the Board in 2016 and Mr. Nicolaisen,
who is not standing for re-election at the annual meeting of shareholders, is
independent. Mr. Gorman, our Chairman and CEO, and Messrs. Hirano and Tamakoshi,
who were designated pursuant to the Investor Agreement with MUFG, have not been
determined independent.</FONT></P>
<P align=right><FONT face=Arial size=2 color=#b3b5b8>Morgan Stanley 2017 Proxy
Statement&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2 color=#007BC4>29</FONT></P>
<HR align=center width="100%" noShade SIZE=2>

<DIV style="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE: always"></DIV><BR>
<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=2><A href="#toc">Table of Contents</A></FONT></B></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=1 color=#b3b5b8>CORPORATE GOVERNANCE</FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>To assess independence, the Board was
provided with information about relationships between the independent directors
(and their immediate family members and affiliated entities) and Morgan Stanley
and its affiliates, including information about the director&#146;s professional
experience and affiliations. In making its determination as to the independent
directors, the Board reviewed the categories of relationships between Morgan
Stanley and the directors described above and the following specific
relationships under those Director Independence Standards:</FONT></P>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Commercial
      relationships (such as financial services offered by the Company to
      clients in the ordinary course of the Company&#146;s business) in the last
      three years between Morgan Stanley and entities where the directors are
      employees or executive officers, or their immediate family members are
      executive officers (Messrs. Bowles and Kleinfeld, Ms. Olayan and Dr.
      Tyson). In each case the fees the Company received were in compliance with
      the Director Independence Standards and the NYSE rules, and did not exceed
      the greater of $1 million or 2% of such other entity&#146;s consolidated gross
      revenues in any of the last three years and were considered
  immaterial.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width=99%>Director&#146;s
      utilization of Morgan Stanley products and services offered by the Company
      as a client of the Company (such as Wealth Management brokerage accounts
      and investments in funds sponsored by the Company) in the ordinary course
      of the Company&#146;s business on terms and conditions substantially similar to
      those provided to unaffiliated third parties (Messrs. Glocer and Herz, Ms.
      Miscik, Mr. Nally, Ms. Olayan, Messrs. Owens and Traquina, Dr. Tyson and
      Mr. Wilkins). In each case the provision of such products and services was
      in compliance with the Director Independence Standards and the NYSE rules
      and was considered immaterial.</TD></TR></TABLE>
<br>
<TABLE style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 2pt; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid" noWrap align=left width="100%" bgColor=#ffffff><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt" face=Arial color=#007bc4><A NAME="p30"></A>Director Attendance at Annual
    Meeting</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Corporate Governance Policies state
that directors are expected to attend annual meetings of shareholders. All 15
directors who were on the Board at the time, including all current directors who
were nominees at the time, attended the 2016 annual meeting of
shareholders.</FONT></P>
<TABLE style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 2pt; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid" noWrap align=left width="100%" bgColor=#ffffff><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt" face=Arial color=#007bc4><A NAME="p30-1"></A>Board Meetings and
  Committees</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt">Board Meetings</FONT></B></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Our Board met 19 times during 2016. Each
current director attended at least 75% of the total number of meetings of the
Board and committees on which such director served that were held during 2016
while the director was a member. In addition to Board and committee meetings,
our directors also discharge their duties through, among other things, less
formal group communications, including discussions, briefings and educational
sessions, with the Independent Lead Director, Chairman of the Board and CEO,
members of senior management and others as appropriate regarding matters of
interest.</FONT></P>
<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt">Committees</FONT></B></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Board&#146;s standing committees, their
membership and the number of meetings in 2016 are set forth below. Charters for
each of our standing committees are available at our corporate governance
webpage at www.morganstanley.com/about-us-governance.</FONT></P>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">All members of the Audit Committee, the
      CMDS Committee and the Nominating and Governance Committee satisfy the
      standards of independence applicable to members of such committees,
      including NYSE listing standards.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">Each member of the CMDS Committee is a
      &#147;non-employee director&#148; as defined in Section 16 of the Securities
      Exchange Act of 1934 and an &#147;outside director&#148; as defined by Section
      162(m) of the Internal Revenue Code.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">The Board has determined that all members
      of the Audit Committee are independent and &#147;financially literate&#148; within
      the meaning of the NYSE listing standards and &#147;audit committee financial
      experts&#148; within the meaning of the SEC rules.</TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%">All members of the Risk Committee and Operations and
      Technology Committee are non-employee directors and a majority of the
      members of such committees satisfy the independence requirements of the
      Company and the NYSE, and the Risk Committee membership satisfies other
      applicable legal and regulatory criteria.</TD></TR></TABLE>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2 color=#007BC4>30&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2 color=#b3b5b8>Morgan Stanley 2017 Proxy Statement</FONT></P>
<HR align=center width="100%" noShade SIZE=2>

      the Company&#146;s consolidated financial statements and system of internal
      controls.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="padding-bottom: 4pt;PADDING-LEFT: 30pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" face=arial color=#007cc3>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Oversees risk management and
      risk assessment guidelines in coordination with the Board, Risk Committee
      and Operations and Technology Committee and reviews the major legal and
      compliance risk exposures of the Company and the steps management has
      taken to monitor and control such exposures.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="padding-bottom: 4pt;PADDING-LEFT: 30pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" face=arial color=#007cc3>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Selects, determines the
      compensation of, evaluates and, when appropriate, replaces the independent
      auditor.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="padding-bottom: 4pt;PADDING-LEFT: 30pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" face=arial color=#007cc3>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Oversees the qualifications,
      independence and performance of the independent auditor, and pre-approves
      audit and permitted non-audit services.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="padding-bottom: 4pt;PADDING-LEFT: 30pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" face=arial color=#007cc3>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Oversees the performance of

      Director), who reports functionally to the Audit Committee, and the
      internal audit function.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="padding-bottom: 4pt;PADDING-LEFT: 30pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" face=arial color=#007cc3>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>After review, recommends to
      the Board the acceptance and inclusion of the annual audited consolidated
      financial statements in the Company&#146;s Annual Report on Form
      10-K.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="PADDING-LEFT: 30pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" face=arial color=#007cc3>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>See also &#147;Audit
      Matters.&#148;</FONT></DIV></TD></TR></TABLE><BR>

    <TD STYLE="width: 15%; padding-right: 15pt">
      <P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial color=#007bc4 size=2>RISK<SUP>(2)</SUP></FONT></B></P></TD>
    <TD width="85%" bgColor=#ffffff>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
  <TR style="PADDING-RIGHT: 2pt; PADDING-LEFT: 2pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 2pt; PADDING-TOP: 2pt">
    <TD NOWRAP STYLE="border-top: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; border-left: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; vertical-align: top; width: 15%; padding-right: 15pt">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial color=#007bc4 size=2>Current
      Members<BR></FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Perry M. Traquina
      (Chair)<BR>Alistair Darling<BR>Nobuyuki Hirano<BR>Jami Miscik<BR>Donald T.
      Nicolaisen</FONT></P>
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial color=#007bc4 size=2>Meetings Held in 2016
      </FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>7</FONT></P></TD>
    <TD style="BORDER-RIGHT: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; BORDER-TOP: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; BORDER-BOTTOM: #b3b5b8 1pt solid" vAlign=top width="85%">
      <DIV align=left><FONT face=Arial color=#007bc4 size=2>Primary
      Responsibilities</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="padding-bottom: 4pt;PADDING-LEFT: 30pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" face=arial color=#007cc3>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Oversees the Company&#146;s
      global ERM framework.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="padding-bottom: 4pt; PADDING-LEFT: 30pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" face=arial color=#007cc3>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Oversees the Company&#146;s
      capital, liquidity and funding planning and strategy.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="padding-bottom: 4pt; PADDING-LEFT: 30pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" face=arial color=#007cc3>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Oversees the major risk
      exposures of the Company, including market, credit, operational,
      liquidity, model, funding and reputational risk, against established risk
      measurement methodologies and the steps management has taken to monitor
      and control such exposures and reviews significant new product risk,
      emerging risks and regulatory matters.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="padding-bottom: 4pt; PADDING-LEFT: 30pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" face=arial color=#007cc3>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Oversees the Company&#146;s risk
      appetite statement, including risk limits and tolerances and the ongoing
      alignment of the Risk Appetite Statement with the Company&#146;s strategy and
      capital plans.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="padding-bottom: 4pt; PADDING-LEFT: 30pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" face=arial color=#007cc3>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Reviews the contingency
      funding plan, internal capital adequacy assessment process, Comprehensive
      Capital Analysis and Review, Dodd-Frank Act Stress Testing submissions and
      Title I Resolution Plan.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="padding-bottom: 4pt; PADDING-LEFT: 30pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" face=arial color=#007cc3>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Oversees risk management and
      risk assessment policies and guidelines.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="padding-bottom: 4pt; PADDING-LEFT: 30pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" face=arial color=#007cc3>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>Oversees the performance of
      the CRO (who reports to the Risk Committee and the CEO) and the risk
      management function.</FONT></DIV>
      <DIV style="PADDING-LEFT: 30pt; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; TEXT-INDENT: -14.5pt"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" face=arial color=#007cc3>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2>See also &#147;Board Leadership
      Structure and Role in Risk Oversight&#151;Board Role in Risk
      Oversight.&#148;</FONT></DIV></TD></TR></TABLE><BR>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 2pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT color=#007bc4 size=1><SUP>(1)</SUP></FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt; PADDING-TOP: 2pt" vAlign=top width="99%"><FONT size=1 face=Arial>Effective December 1, 2016, Mr. Nally joined the
      Audit Committee.</FONT></TD></TR>

    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 2pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT color=#007bc4 size=1><SUP>(2)</SUP></FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt; PADDING-TOP: 2pt" vAlign=top width="99%"><FONT size=1 face=Arial>Effective February 1, 2017, Mr. Traquina joined
      and was appointed Chair of the Risk Committee. Effective May 17, 2016, Mr.
      Darling joined the Risk Committee when Dr. Tyson concluded service on the
      Board and the Risk Committee.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><BR>
<TABLE style="LINE-HEIGHT: normal; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 2pt; WIDTH: 100%; BORDER-BOTTOM: #007bc4 1pt solid; TEXT-ALIGN: left" noWrap><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt" face=Arial color=#007cc4><A NAME="p33"></A>Board
      Leadership Structure and Role in Risk
Oversight</FONT></B></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P align=left><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt" face=Arial>Board Leadership
Structure</FONT></B></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Board is responsible for reviewing the
Company&#146;s leadership structure. As set forth in the Corporate Governance
Policies, the Board believes that the Company and its shareholders are best
served by maintaining the flexibility to have any individual serve as Chairman
of the Board based on what is in the best interests of the Company at a given
point in time, taking into consideration, among other things:</FONT></P>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The composition of the
      Board;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The role of the Company&#146;s
      Independent Lead Director;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Company&#146;s strong corporate
      governance practices;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The CEO&#146;s working relationship with
      the Board; and</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The challenges specific to the
      Company.</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Board has determined that the
appointment of a strong Independent Lead Director (as described below), together
with a combined Chairman and CEO, serve the best interests of the Company and
its shareholders. By serving in both positions, the CEO and Chairman is able to
draw on his detailed knowledge of the Company to provide the Board, in
coordination with the Independent Lead Director, leadership in focusing its
discussions and review of the Company&#146;s strategy. In addition, a combined role
of CEO and Chairman ensures that the Company presents its message and strategy
to shareholders, employees and clients with a unified voice. The Board believes
that it is in the best interest of the Company and its shareholders for Mr.
Gorman to serve as Chairman and CEO at this time, considering the strong role of
our Independent Lead Director and other corporate governance practices providing
independent oversight of management as set forth below.</FONT></P>
<P align=right><FONT face=Arial color=#b3b5b8 size=2>Morgan Stanley 2017 Proxy
Statement&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT><FONT face=arial color=#007bc4 size=2>33</FONT></P>
<HR align=center width="100%" noShade SIZE=2>

<DIV style="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE: always"></DIV><BR>
<P align=left><A href="#toc"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Table of
Contents</FONT></B></A></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial color=#b3b5b8 size=1>CORPORATE
GOVERNANCE</FONT></P>

<P align=left><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt" face=Arial>Independent Lead
Director</FONT></B></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Corporate Governance Policies provide
for an independent and active Independent Lead Director who is appointed and
reviewed annually by the independent directors with clearly defined leadership
authority and responsibilities. Our Independent Lead Director, Erskine B.
Bowles, was appointed by our other independent directors and has
responsibilities including:</FONT></P>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Presiding at all meetings of the
      Board at which the Chairman is not present, including at executive
      sessions of the independent and non-management directors;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Having the authority to call, and
      lead, sessions composed only of non-management directors or independent
      directors;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Serving as liaison between the
      Chairman and the independent directors;</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Soliciting non-management directors
      for advice on agenda items for meetings of the Board;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Communicating with the Chairman
      between meetings and acting as a &#147;sounding board&#148; and
    advisor;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Advising the Chairman of the Board
      on the Board&#146;s informational needs;</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Approving the types and forms of
      information sent to the Board;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Collaborating with the Chairman in
      developing the agendas for meetings of the Board and approving Board
      meeting agendas and the schedule of Board meetings to assure that there is
      sufficient time for discussion of all agenda items and requesting, if
      necessary, the inclusion of additional agenda items; </FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Making himself available, if
      requested, to meet with the Company&#146;s primary
  regulators;</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Making himself available, if
      requested by major shareholders, for consultation and direct
      communication;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Leading the annual evaluation of the
      performance and effectiveness of the Board;</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%" style="PADDING-BOTTOM :4pt">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Consulting with the Chair of the
      Nominating and Governance Committee on Board succession planning and Board
      committee appointments;</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Interviewing candidates for the
      Board; and</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Consulting with the Chair of the
      CMDS Committee on the annual evaluation and performance of the
      CEO.</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P align=left><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt" face=Arial>Independent Oversight
of Management</FONT></B></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Company&#146;s corporate governance
practices and policies ensure substantial independent oversight of management.
For instance:</FONT></P>
<TABLE style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Arial; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse; TEXT-ALIGN: left" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Board has a majority of
      independent and non-management directors.</FONT></B><FONT face=Arial size=2> Eleven of the 14 director nominees are independent as defined by
      the NYSE listing standards and the Company&#146;s more stringent Director
      Independence Standards. Thirteen of 14 director nominees are
      non-management directors. All of the Company&#146;s directors are elected
      annually.</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Board&#146;s key standing
      committees are composed solely of non-management
      directors.</FONT></B><FONT face=Arial size=2> The Audit Committee, the
      CMDS Committee, and the Nominating and Governance Committee are each
      composed solely of independent directors. The Operations and Technology
      Committee and Risk Committee are chaired by independent directors and
      consist of a majority of independent directors and include only
      non-management directors. The committees provide independent oversight of
      management.</FONT></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 5pt; PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 4pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 9.5pt" color=#007bc4>&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Board&#146;s non-management
      directors meet regularly in executive session.</FONT></B><FONT face=Arial size=2> The non-management directors meet regularly in executive session
      without management present and, consistent with the NYSE listing
      standards, at least annually, the independent directors meet in executive
      session. These sessions are chaired by the Independent Lead
      Director.</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<P align=left><FONT face=arial color=#007bc4 size=2>34&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</FONT><FONT face=Arial color=#b3b5b8 size=2>Morgan Stanley 2017 Proxy Statement</FONT></P>
<HR align=center width="100%" noShade SIZE=2>

<P align=left><A href="#toc"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Table of
Contents</FONT></B></A></P>
<P align=right><FONT face=Arial color=#b3b5b8 size=1>CORPORATE
GOVERNANCE</FONT></P>
<P align=left><B><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 11pt" face=Arial>Board Role in Risk
Oversight</FONT></B></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Effective risk management is vital to the
success of Morgan Stanley. The Board has oversight for the Company&#146;s global ERM
framework, which integrates the roles of the Company&#146;s risk management functions
into a holistic enterprise to facilitate the incorporation of risk assessment
into decision-making processes across the Company, and is responsible for
helping to ensure that the Company&#146;s risks are managed in a sound manner. The
Board regularly reviews the Company&#146;s risks and the responsibilities of
management and the Board committees to assist the Board in its risk
oversight.</FONT></P>
<DIV align=center>
<TABLE style="LINE-HEIGHT: normal; BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="95%" border=0>

  <TR>
    <TD NOWRAP COLSPAN="15" STYLE="border-top: #007bc4 1pt solid; border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid; padding-bottom: 2pt; width: 98%; padding-top: 2pt; background-color: #e6e7e8; width: 98%; padding-left: 4pt">
      <P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=1>Coordination Among Board
      Committees Regarding Risk Oversight</FONT></B></P></TD>
    <TD NOWRAP STYLE="width: 1%;  border-top: #007bc4 1pt solid; border-bottom: #b3b5b8 1pt solid;  background-color: rgb(230,231,232)"></TD></TR>
  <TR style="LINE-HEIGHT: 6pt">
    <TD NOWRAP STYLE="width: 1%; background-color: rgb(230,231,232)">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>

    <TD NOWRAP STYLE="width: 1%; background-color: rgb(230,231,232)"></TD>

    <TD style="WIDTH: 20%; BACKGROUND-COLOR: #007cc3; TEXT-ALIGN: center" noWrap width="16%" bgColor=#007bc4 colSpan=2 vAlign=middle><FONT color=#ffffff><STRONG><FONT face=Arial size=1>Board of
      Directors</FONT></STRONG></FONT></TD>
    <TD style="WIDTH: 1%; PADDING-TOP: 4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left" noWrap width="1%" bgColor=#e6e7e8></TD>
    <TD style="WIDTH: 19%; PADDING-TOP: 4pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left" noWrap width="17%" bgColor=#e6e7e8 colSpan=2>

      <DIV style="PADDING-LEFT: 15pt; FONT-SIZE: 7.5pt; TEXT-INDENT: -13pt; TEXT-ALIGN: left"><FONT style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt; FONT-SIZE: 7pt" color=#007cc3>&#9679;</FONT><FONT face=Arial size=1><FONT face=Arial size=1>Governance
