<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=2><A href="#toc">Table of Contents</A></FONT></B></p>
<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial style="font-size: 22pt"><FONT color=#007bc4><A NAME="annexb"></A>ANNEX
B</FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P align=center><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>MORGAN STANLEY<BR></FONT></B><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>DIRECTORS&#146; EQUITY CAPITAL ACCUMULATION PLAN<BR>(As Proposed to
Be Amended and Restated)</FONT></B></P>

<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 1. Purpose</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>Morgan Stanley, a Delaware corporation
(the &#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Company</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148;), hereby adopts the Morgan Stanley Directors&#146; Equity Capital
Accumulation Plan (the &#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Plan</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148;). The purpose of the Plan is to promote the long-term growth
and financial success of the Company by attracting, motivating and retaining
non-employee directors of outstanding ability and assisting the Company in
promoting a greater identity of interest between the Company&#146;s non-employee
directors and its stockholders.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>Capitalized terms used herein without
definition have the meanings ascribed thereto in Section 24.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 2. Eligibility and Limitation
on Director Compensation</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>Only directors of the Company who are not
employees of the Company or any affiliate of the Company (the &#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Eligible Directors</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148;) shall
participate in the Plan.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>Notwithstanding anything in this Plan to
the contrary, the aggregate dollar value of Awards granted and Retainers paid to
any individual Eligible Director for any Annual Service Period shall not exceed
seven hundred and fifty thousand dollars ($750,000). The value of any Awards
shall be determined based on the Fair Market Value of a share of Stock on the
grant date.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 3. Plan
Operation</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(a) <U>Administration</U>. Other than as
provided in Section 5(c)(v), the Plan requires no discretionary action by any
administrative body with regard to any transaction under the Plan. To the
extent, if any, that questions of administration arise, these shall be resolved
by the Board. The Board may, in its discretion, delegate to the Chief Financial
Officer, the Chief Legal Officer, the Secretary of the Company or to one or more
officers of the Company any or all authority and responsibility to act pursuant
to the Plan. All references to the &#147;Plan Administrators&#148; in the Plan shall refer
to the Board, or the Chief Financial Officer, the Chief Legal Officer, the
Secretary or to one or more officers of the Company if the Board has delegated
its authority pursuant to this Section 3(a). The determination of the Plan
Administrators on all matters within their authority relating to the Plan shall
be conclusive.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(b) <U>No Liability</U>. The Plan
Administrators shall not be liable for any action or determination made in good
faith with respect to the Plan or any award hereunder, and the Company shall
indemnify and hold harmless the Plan Administrators from all losses and expenses
(including reasonable attorneys&#146; fees) arising from the assertion or judicial
determination of any such liability.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 4. Shares of Stock Subject to
the Plan</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(a) <U>Stock</U>. Awards under the Plan
shall relate to shares of Stock.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(b) <U>Shares Available for Awards</U>.
Subject to Section 4(c) (relating to adjustments upon changes in
capitalization), as of any date, the total number of shares of Stock with
respect to which awards may be granted under the Plan shall be equal to the
excess (if any) of (i) 3,450,000 shares over (ii) the sum of (A) the number of
shares subject to outstanding awards granted
under the Plan and (B) the number of shares previously issued pursuant to the Plan. In accordance with (and
without limitation upon) the preceding sentence, shares of Stock covered by
awards granted under the Plan that are canceled or expire unexercised shall
again become available for awards under the Plan. Shares of Stock that shall be
issuable pursuant to the awards granted under the Plan shall be authorized and
unissued shares, treasury shares or shares of Stock purchased by, or on behalf
of, the Company in open-market transactions.</FONT></P>
<P align=right><FONT face=Arial size=2><FONT color=#b3b5b8>Morgan Stanley 2017
Proxy Statement</FONT></FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2></FONT>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<FONT face=Arial size=2><FONT color=#007bc4>B-1</FONT></FONT></P>
<HR align=center width="100%" noShade SIZE=2>

<DIV style="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE: always"></DIV><BR>
<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=2><A href="#toc">Table of Contents</A></FONT></B></p>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=1><FONT color=#b3b5b8>ANNEX
B</FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(c) <U>Adjustments</U>. In the event of
any merger, reorganization, recapitalization, consolidation, sale or other
distribution of substantially all of the assets of the Company, any stock
dividend, split, spin-off, split-up, split-off, distribution of cash, securities
or other property by the Company, or other change in the Company&#146;s corporate
structure affecting the Stock, then the following shall be automatically
adjusted in order to prevent dilution or enlargement of the benefits or
potential benefits intended to be awarded under the Plan: </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(i) the aggregate number of shares of
Stock reserved for issuance under the Plan; </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(ii) the number of shares of Stock subject
to outstanding awards; </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(iii) the number of Stock Units credited
pursuant to Section 6 and Section 9 of the Plan; </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(iv) the per share purchase price of Stock
subject to any stock options granted pursuant to the Plan; and </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(v) the number of shares to be granted
pursuant to any other automatic awards that may be provided for under the Plan
in the future.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(d) <U>Types of Award</U>. The Company&#146;s
stockholders originally approved the Plan on April 19, 1996, and approved
amendments to the Plan on March 19, 2002. The types of award authorized by the
stockholders under the Plan are Director Stock, Stock Units, shares of Stock
awarded at an Eligible Director&#146;s election pursuant to Section 11 and stock
options.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 5. Stock Options</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(a) Effective as of February 8, 2005 (the
&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Stock Option Transition Date</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148;), no additional stock options will be awarded under the
Plan.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(b) Section 5(a) shall not impair the
rights of any person in any stock option that was awarded under the Plan prior
to the Stock Option Transition Date. All such stock options shall remain subject
to the terms and conditions applicable thereto.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(c) The following terms and conditions
apply to stock options issued under the Plan, including without limitation all
stock options issued prior to the Stock Option Transition Date: </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(i) <U>Nontransferability</U>. No stock
option granted pursuant to the Plan shall be sold, assigned or otherwise
transferred by an Eligible Director other than by will or the laws of descent or
distribution and any such stock option may be exercised during the Eligible
Director&#146;s lifetime only by such Eligible Director.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(ii) <U>Limitation on Exercise</U>. No
stock option granted pursuant to this Plan may be exercised for a period of six
(6) months from the date such stock option was granted.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(iii) <U>Effect of
Termination</U>.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 45pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(A) If an Eligible Director&#146;s service as a
director of the Company terminates for a reason other than for Cause, then any
stock option granted to such Eligible Director shall remain exercisable
following the date of such Eligible Director&#146;s termination of service in
accordance with the following provisions: </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 60pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(a) Disability, Normal Retirement or
Death. If service terminates by reason of Disability, Normal Retirement or
death, until the expiration date of the stock option.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 60pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(b) Other. If service terminates for any
other reason (except for Cause), until the earlier of 90 days after the
termination date and the expiration date of the stock option.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 45pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(B) If an Eligible Director is terminated
for Cause, all stock options granted under the Plan to such Eligible Director
shall be canceled and shall no longer be exercisable, effective on the date of
such Eligible Director&#146;s termination for Cause.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(iv) <U>Expiration Date of Stock Options</U>. All
stock options granted under the Plan shall expire on the tenth anniversary of
the date on which they are granted.</FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2><FONT color=#007bc4>B-2</FONT></FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2></FONT> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<FONT face=Arial size=2><FONT color=#b3b5b8>Morgan Stanley 2017 Proxy Statement</FONT></FONT></P>
<HR align=center width="100%" noShade SIZE=2>

<DIV style="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE: always"></DIV><BR>
<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=2><A href="#toc">Table of Contents</A></FONT></B></p>
<P STYLE="text-align: right"><FONT face=Arial size=1><FONT color=#b3b5b8>ANNEX
B</FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(v) <U>Extension of Exercisability</U>.
Notwithstanding any other provision hereof, the Board shall have the authority,
in its discretion, to amend any outstanding stock option granted pursuant to the
Plan to extend the exercisability thereof; <I>provided</I>, <I>however</I>, that no such amendment shall cause such stock option to remain
exercisable beyond its original expiration date.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(d) Notwithstanding Section 5(a), stock
options remain one of the types of award that the stockholders of the Company
have authorized for the Plan, and Section 5(a) shall not impair the authority of
the Board under Section 15 to amend the Plan in the future to provide for awards
of stock options without obtaining additional stockholder approval.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 6. Initial and Annual
Awards</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(a) <U>Initial Awards</U>. On the first
day of the calendar month following the month in which any person becomes an
Eligible Director, otherwise than by reason of being elected to the Board at an
Annual Meeting, such Eligible Director shall be entitled to receive a number of
Initial Stock Units obtained by dividing (x) $250,000 prorated for service
during the period beginning on the first day of the calendar month during which
such person becomes an Eligible Director until the last day of the calendar
month immediately preceding the calendar month during which the first
anniversary of the immediately preceding Annual Meeting will occur by (y) the
Fair Market Value of a share of Stock on the first day of the calendar month
following the month in which such person becomes an Eligible Director;
<I>provided</I>,
<I>however</I>, that if
such a person is elected, appointed or otherwise becomes an Eligible Director
less than 60 days prior to the Annual Meeting in any year, then such Eligible
Director shall not receive Initial Stock Units pursuant to this Section 6(a).
50% of the Initial Stock Units awarded to an Eligible Director pursuant to this
Section 6(a) shall be credited to the Eligible Director&#146;s Career Stock Unit
Account and the remaining 50% of the Initial Stock Units shall be credited to
the Eligible Director&#146;s Current Stock Unit Account.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(b) <U>Subsequent Awards</U>. As of the
date of each Annual Meeting, each Eligible Director, including, without
limitation, any Eligible Director who becomes a member of the Board by reason of
being elected to the Board at such Annual Meeting, shall be entitled to receive
a number of Annual Stock Units obtained by dividing $250,000 by the Fair Market
Value of a share of Stock on the date of such Annual Meeting; <I>provided</I>, that such Eligible
Director shall continue to serve as a director of the Company after such Annual
Meeting. 50% of the Annual Stock Units awarded to an Eligible Director pursuant
to this Section 6(b) shall be credited to the Eligible Director&#146;s Career Stock
Unit Account and the remaining 50% of the Annual Stock Units shall be credited
to the Eligible Director&#146;s Current Stock Unit Account. Annual Stock Units and
Initial Stock Units credited to the Eligible Director&#146;s Career Stock Unit
Account pursuant to this Section 6(b) or pursuant to Section 6(a) above are
referred to as &#147;<I>Career Stock
Units</I>&#148;. </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(c) <U>Limitation on Transfer</U>. Any
Director Stock awarded under the Plan may not be sold, transferred, pledged,
assigned or otherwise conveyed by an Eligible Director for a period of six (6)
months from the date such Director Stock is awarded. Neither Annual Stock Units
nor Initial Stock Units may be sold, transferred, pledged, assigned or otherwise
conveyed by an Eligible Director. The shares delivered upon conversion of Annual
Stock Units and Initial Stock Units will not be subject to any transfer
restrictions, other than those that may arise under the securities laws or the
Company&#146;s policies.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(d) <U>No Effect on Prior Initial Awards
or Prior Subsequent Awards</U>. The provisions of this Section 6 apply to all
Initial Awards and Subsequent Awards made on or after the Stock Unit Transition
Date. Nothing herein shall alter the grants of Initial Awards and Subsequent
Awards made prior to the Stock Unit Transition Date.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 7. Vesting
Schedule</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(a) <U>Initial Stock Units</U>. The
Initial Stock Units shall be fully vested upon grant.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(b) <U>Annual Stock Units</U>. The Annual
Stock Units shall vest in 12 substantially equal installments on the last day of
each month beginning with the calendar month during which the Annual Meeting is
held, assuming that the Eligible Director continues to serve as a director of
the Company through the last day of the relevant month.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 8. Death, Disability and
Governmental Service</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(a) <U>Death or Disability</U>. All of an
Eligible Director&#146;s unvested Stock Units will vest in full as of the date of the
Eligible Director&#146;s termination of service on the Board due to death or
Disability. Notwithstanding any election made by an Eligible Director on any
Deferral Election Form or any other provision of the Plan, in the event of such
Eligible Director&#146;s death, all amounts credited to such Eligible Director&#146;s Cash
Account, Current Stock Unit Account and Career Stock Unit</FONT></P>
<P align=right><FONT face=Arial size=2><FONT color=#b3b5b8>Morgan Stanley 2017
Proxy Statement</FONT></FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2></FONT>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<FONT face=Arial size=2><FONT color=#007bc4>B-3</FONT></FONT></P>
<HR align=center width="100%" noShade SIZE=2>

<DIV style="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE: always"></DIV><BR>
<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=2><A href="#toc">Table of Contents</A></FONT></B></p>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=1><FONT color=#b3b5b8>ANNEX
B</FONT></FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Account, and any Deferred Amount that has
not yet been credited to such Eligible Director&#146;s Cash Account or Current Stock
Unit Account, will be paid in a lump sum to the Eligible Director&#146;s beneficiary
(or if no beneficiary has been designated, to such Eligible Director&#146;s estate)
upon the Eligible Director&#146;s death, <I>provided</I> that such beneficiary or the
legal representative of such Eligible Director&#146;s estate, as applicable, notifies
the Company of the Eligible Director&#146;s death within 60 days following death.
Following an Eligible Director&#146;s termination of service on the Board due to
Disability, distributions under the Plan will be made as provided in Section
9(e) or Section 9(f), as applicable.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(b) <U>Governmental Service
Resignation</U>. Notwithstanding any election made by an Eligible Director on
any Deferral Form, if an Eligible Director resigns as a director of the Company
as a result of accepting employment at a governmental department or agency,
self-regulatory agency or other public service employer (a &#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Governmental Employer</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148;)
(such resignation is referred to herein as a &#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Governmental Service Resignation</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148;),
then (i) if the Eligible Director provides the Company with satisfactory
evidence demonstrating that as a result of such employment, the divestiture of
his or her continued interest in Company equity awards or continued ownership of
Stock is reasonably necessary to avoid the violation of U.S. federal, state or
local or foreign ethics law or conflicts of interest law applicable to the
Eligible Director at such Governmental Employer, all of an Eligible Director&#146;s
unvested Stock Units will vest in full as of the date of the Eligible Director&#146;s
Governmental Service Resignation, all amounts credited to the Eligible
Director&#146;s Current Stock Unit Account and Career Stock Unit Account will be
distributed in a lump sum in accordance with Section 9(h), and all transfer
restrictions will lift on shares of Director Stock held by the Eligible
Director, on the date of such Governmental Service Resignation, and (ii) if the
Eligible Director provides the Company with satisfactory evidence demonstrating
that as a result of such employment, the divestiture of the Eligible Director&#146;s
continued interest in his or her Cash Account is reasonably necessary to avoid
the violation of U.S. federal, state or local or foreign ethics law or conflicts
of interest law applicable to the Eligible Director at such Governmental
Employer, all amounts credited to the Eligible Director&#146;s Cash Account will be
distributed in a lump sum on the date of such Governmental Service
Resignation.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(c) <U>Governmental Service following
Resignation</U>. Notwithstanding any election made by an Eligible Director on
any Deferral Form, if, following Eligible Director&#146;s Service Termination Date,
the Eligible Director accepts employment with a Governmental Employer, then (i)
upon providing the Company with satisfactory evidence demonstrating that as a
result of such employment the divestiture of the Eligible Director&#146;s continued
interest in Company equity awards or continued ownership of Stock is reasonably
necessary to avoid the violation of U.S. federal, state or local or foreign
ethics law or conflicts of interest law applicable to the Eligible Director at
such Governmental Employer, all amounts credited to the Eligible Director&#146;s
Current Stock Unit Account and Career Stock Unit Account will be distributed in
a lump sum in accordance with Section 9(h), and all transfer restrictions will
lift on shares of Director Stock held by the Director, on the date on which the
Eligible Director provides the Company with such satisfactory evidence, and (ii)
if the Eligible Director provides the Company with satisfactory evidence
demonstrating that as a result of such employment, the divestiture of the
Eligible Director&#146;s continued interest in his or her Cash Account is reasonably
necessary to avoid the violation of U.S. federal, state or local or foreign
ethics law or conflicts of interest law applicable to the Eligible Director at
such Governmental Employer, all amounts credited to the Eligible Director&#146;s Cash
Account will be distributed in a lump sum on the date on which the Eligible
Director provides the Company with such satisfactory evidence.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 9. Deferral Elections and
Distributions</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(a) <U>Deferral of Retainers</U>. An
Eligible Director may make a Deferral Election to defer receipt of all or part
of such Eligible Director&#146;s Retainers for a given service period. An Eligible
Director may make such a Deferral Election by submitting a Deferral Election
Form to the Secretary, indicating: </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(i) the Deferred Amount or a percentage of
such Retainer to be deferred; </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(ii) the Distribution Commencement Date,
in accordance with Section 9(e); and </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(iii) whether distributions are to be made
in a lump sum or installments, in accordance with Section 9(g). </FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Deferral Election Forms must be submitted
prior to the start of the calendar year during which the services giving rise to
such Retainer to be deferred begin;</FONT> <I><FONT face=Arial size=2>provided</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>,</FONT><B><FONT face=Arial size=2></FONT></B> <I><FONT face=Arial size=2>however</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>, that in the case of an Eligible Director who is newly elected or
appointed to the Board, such Eligible Director&#146;s Deferral Election Form relating
to the Retainer earned during the service period commencing on the date of such
election or appointment may be submitted within 30 days after the date of
such</FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2><FONT color=#007bc4>B-4</FONT></FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2></FONT> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<FONT face=Arial size=2><FONT color=#b3b5b8>Morgan Stanley 2017 Proxy Statement</FONT></FONT></P>
<HR align=center width="100%" noShade SIZE=2>

<P align=left><B><FONT face=Arial size=2><A href="#toc">Table of Contents</A></FONT></B></p>
<P STYLE="text-align: right"><FONT face=Arial size=1><FONT color=#b3b5b8>ANNEX
B</FONT></FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>election or appointment. In all cases, a
Deferral Election Form shall be effective only with respect to Retainers that
are earned after the Deferral Election is made. An Eligible Director may make
only one Deferral Election covering Retainers to be earned during a given
service period (so that an Eligible Director may not, for example, make one
Deferral Election relating to the Annual Retainer and a different Deferral
Election relating to a Committee Retainer). Deferral Elections (including
indications on the Deferral Election Form as to Distribution Commencement Date
and form of distributions), once made, shall be irrevocable. Notwithstanding the
foregoing, a Deferral Election may be superseded with respect to future
deferrals of an Eligible Director&#146;s Retainers by submitting a new Deferral
Election Form to the Secretary, in which case such new Deferral Election shall
be effective starting with the Retainer earned in the service period that begins
in the calendar year following the calendar year in which such new Deferral
Election Form is submitted.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(b) <U>Crediting of Deferrals of
Retainers</U>. Deferrals of an Eligible Director&#146;s Retainers shall be allocated
to a Current Stock Unit Account. As of each Retainer Payment Date, the Company
shall credit the Eligible Director&#146;s Current Stock Unit Account with a number of
Elective Stock Units determined by dividing (X) the Deferred Amount of Retainers
that otherwise would be paid in cash on such Retainer Payment Date by (Y) the
Fair Market Value of a share of Stock on such Retainer Payment Date.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(c) <U>Deferrals of Current Stock
Units</U>. An Eligible Director may make a Deferral Election to defer receipt of
the Current Stock Units to be earned for a given service period by submitting a
Deferral Election Form to the Secretary indicating: </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(i) the Distribution Commencement Date, in
accordance with Section 9(e); and </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(ii) whether distributions are to be made
in a lump sum or installments, in accordance with Section 9(g). </FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>A Deferral Election pursuant to this
Section 9(c) must relate to all Current Stock Units to be earned by an Eligible
Director during a given service period. Deferral Election Forms must be
submitted prior to the start of the calendar year during which the services
giving rise to such Current Stock Units to be deferred begin;</FONT> <I><FONT face=Arial size=2>provided</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>,</FONT> <I><FONT face=Arial size=2>however</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>, that in the case
of an Eligible Director who is newly elected or appointed to the Board, such
Eligible Director&#146;s Deferral Election Form relating to the Current Stock Units
earned during the service period commencing on the date of such election or
appointment (that is, 50% of the Eligible Director&#146;s Initial Stock Units) may be
submitted within 30 days after the date of such election or appointment. In all
cases, a Deferral Election Form shall be effective only with respect to Current
Stock Units that are earned after the Deferral Election is made. Deferral
Elections (including indications on the Deferral Election Form as to
Distribution Commencement Date and form of distributions), once made, shall be
irrevocable. Notwithstanding the foregoing, a Deferral Election may be
superseded with respect to future deferrals of an Eligible Director&#146;s Current
Stock Units by submitting a new Deferral Election Form to the Secretary, in
which case such new Deferral Election shall be effective starting with the
Current Stock Units earned in the service period that begins in the calendar
year following the calendar year in which such new Deferral Election Form is
submitted.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(d) <U>Deferrals of Career Stock
Units</U>. An Eligible Director may elect to defer receipt of the Career Stock
Units to be earned for a given service period by submitting a Deferral Election
Form to the Secretary indicating: </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(i) the Distribution Commencement Date for
such Career Stock Unit Account, in accordance with Section 9(f); and </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(ii) whether distributions are to be made
in a lump sum or installments, in accordance with Section 9(g).</FONT></P>

<P ALIGN="LEFT" ><FONT face=Arial size=2>A Deferral
Election pursuant to this Section 9(d) must relate to all Career Stock Units to
be earned by an Eligible Director during a given service period. Deferral
Election Forms must be submitted prior to the start of the calendar year during
which the services giving rise to such Career Stock Units to be deferred
begin;</FONT> <I><FONT face=Arial size=2>provided</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>,</FONT><B><I><FONT face=Arial size=2></FONT></I></B> <I><FONT face=Arial size=2>however</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>, that in the case of an
Eligible Director who is newly elected or appointed to the Board, such Eligible
Director&#146;s Deferral Election Form relating to the Career Stock Units earned
during the service period commencing on the date of such election or appointment
(that is, 50% of the Eligible Director&#146;s Initial Stock Units) may be submitted
within 30 days after the date of such election or appointment. In all cases, a
Deferral Election Form shall be effective only with respect to the Career Stock
Units that are earned after the Deferral Election is made. Deferral Elections
(including indications on the Deferral Election Form as to Distribution
Commencement Date and form of distributions), once made, shall be irrevocable.
Notwithstanding the foregoing, a Deferral</FONT></P>

Proxy Statement</FONT></FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2></FONT>
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<FONT face=Arial size=2><FONT color=#007bc4>B-5</FONT></FONT></P>

<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=1><FONT color=#b3b5b8>ANNEX
B</FONT></FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Election relating to Career Stock Units
may be superseded with respect to future deferrals by submitting a new Deferral
Election Form to the Secretary, in which case such new Deferral Election shall
be effective starting with the Career Stock Units earned in the service period
that begins in the calendar year following the calendar year in which such new
Deferral Election Form is submitted.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(e) <U>Distribution Commencement Date for
Current Stock Unit Account</U>. Each Eligible Director shall designate on the
Deferral Election Form one of the following dates as a Distribution Commencement
Date with respect to amounts credited to the Current Stock Unit Account
thereafter: </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(i) such Eligible Director&#146;s Service
Termination Date; </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(ii) the earlier of (x) a calendar year
specified by such Eligible Director (which, if the Deferral Election relates to
Elective Stock Units, shall not be earlier than the calendar year following the
year in which occurs the final Retainer Payment Date of the relevant Deferred
Amount and, if the Deferral Election relates to Current Stock Units, shall not
be earlier than the calendar year following the year in which occurs the first
anniversary of the date of grant of the relevant Current Stock Units) and (y)
the fifth calendar year following the year in which the Eligible Director&#146;s
Service Termination Date occurs; or </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(iii) the earlier to occur of (i) or
(ii)(x).
</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 0pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>
For the avoidance of doubt, it is noted that an Eligible Director who
submits separate Deferral Elections for Retainers and Current Stock Units to be
earned during a given service period may designate a separate Distribution
Commencement Date for each deferral. Distributions from an Eligible Director&#146;s
Current Stock Unit Account in respect of Current Stock Units as to which an
Eligible Director has not made a Deferral Election will be made, subject to the
other provisions of this Plan, on the first anniversary of the date of
grant.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(f) <U>Distribution Commencement Date for
Career Stock Unit Account</U>. Notwithstanding any provision to the contrary in
this Plan or any Deferral Election Form, no amounts credited to an Eligible
Director&#146;s Career Stock Unit Account shall be distributed prior to such Eligible
Director&#146;s Service Termination Date. Each Eligible Director may designate on the
Deferral Election Form for such Eligible Director&#146;s Career Stock Unit Account
one of the following dates as a Distribution Commencement Date with respect to
amounts credited to the Career Stock Unit Account: </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(i) such Eligible Director&#146;s Service
Termination Date; or </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(ii) any of the second through fifth
calendar years following the year in which the Eligible Director&#146;s Service
Termination Date occurs.</FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Distributions from an Eligible Director&#146;s
Career Stock Unit Account in respect of Career Stock Units as to which an
Eligible Director has not made a Deferral Election will be made, subject to the
other provisions of this Plan, on the Eligible Director&#146;s Service Termination
Date.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(g) <U>Distribution Method</U>. An
Eligible Director shall state on each Deferral Election Form whether
distributions that are subject to such Deferral Election Form shall be made in:
</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(i) a lump sum; or </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(ii) no more than 10 annual
installments.</FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2>Where an Eligible Director&#146;s Distribution
Commencement Date is such Eligible Director&#146;s Service Termination Date, the lump
sum or first annual installment, as applicable, will be paid upon the Eligible
Director&#146;s Service Termination Date. The amount to be distributed in any
installment pursuant to a specific Deferral Election Form shall be determined by
dividing the number of Stock Units in the Career Stock Unit Account or Current
Stock Unit Account, as the case may be, that are subject to such Deferral
Election Form by the number of remaining installments. If an Eligible Director
receives a distribution on an installment basis, undistributed Deferred Amounts
shall remain subject to the provisions of this Section 9.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(h) <U>Form of Distributions</U>. All
distributions from the Cash Account shall be paid in cash. Distributions made
from the Current Stock Unit Account and the Career Stock Unit Account shall be
for a number of whole shares of Stock equal to the number of whole Stock Units
to be distributed and cash in lieu of any fractional share (determined by using
the Fair Market Value of a share of Stock on the date on which such
distributions are distributed).</FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2><FONT color=#007bc4>B-6</FONT></FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2></FONT> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<FONT face=Arial size=2><FONT color=#b3b5b8>Morgan Stanley 2017 Proxy Statement</FONT></FONT></P>

<P align=right><FONT face=Arial size=1><FONT color=#b3b5b8>ANNEX
B</FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(i) <u>Dividend Equivalents</u>. If there are
Stock Units in an Eligible Director&#146;s Current Stock Unit Account or Career Stock
Unit Account on a dividend record date with respect to the Company&#146;s Stock, the
Current Stock Unit Account or Career Stock Unit Account, as applicable, shall be
credited, on the dividend payment date for such dividend record date, with an
additional number of Stock Units (&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Dividend
Equivalents</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148;) equal to:</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(i) the cash dividend paid on one share of
Stock;</FONT> <I><FONT face=Arial size=2>multiplied by</FONT></I></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(ii) the number of Stock Units in such
Account on such dividend record date; with the product of (i) and (ii) <I>divided by</I></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(iii) the Fair Market Value of a share of
Stock on the dividend payment date. </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 0pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>
Dividend Equivalents credited in respect of
Stock Units subject to vesting shall be fully vested upon grant.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(j) <u>No Effect on Prior Deferral Elections</u>.
The provisions of this Section 9 apply to all Deferral Elections made on or
after the Stock Unit Transition Date. Nothing herein shall alter the terms of
effective Deferral Elections made prior to the Stock Unit Transition
Date.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(k) <u>Date of Payment</u>. Unless the Plan
Administrator determines otherwise, whenever a Deferral Election specifies a
calendar year for payment of all or a portion of a Deferred Amount, such payment
shall be made on January 2 of the specified calendar year.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(l) <u>Rule of Construction for Timing of
Payment</u></FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>.</FONT></I><B><I><FONT face=Arial size=2></FONT></I></B> <FONT face=Arial size=2>Whenever a Deferral Election or
the Plan provides for payment upon a specified event or date, such payment will
be considered to have been timely made, and neither the Eligible Director nor
any of his or her beneficiaries or estate shall have any claim against the
Company for damages based on a delay in payment, and the Firm shall have no
liability to the Eligible Director (or to any of his or her beneficiaries or
estate) in respect of any such delay, as long as payment is made by December 31
of the year in which occurs the applicable specified event or date or, if later,
by the 15th day of the third calendar month following such specified event or
date.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(m) <u>Deferral of Meeting Fees</u>. As of the
Stock Option Transition Date, the Company does not pay Meeting Fees. In the
event that the Company determines in the future to pay Meeting Fees to Eligible
Directors, and in the case of Meeting Fees deferred prior to the Stock Option
Transition Date, the provisions of this Section 9 relating to elective deferrals
of Retainers, and the provisions of Section 11 relating to Stock Elections,
shall apply to such Meeting Fees mutatis mutandis; <I>provided</I>, <I>however</I>, that any Deferred Amount resulting from deferral of all or part of an
Eligible Director&#146;s Meeting Fees (other than Meeting Fees for meetings of the
Board or any committee thereof held on the date of an Annual Meeting) will
initially be credited to the Cash Account as of the date on which the Eligible
Director becomes entitled to payment of the Meeting Fees, shall thereafter be
credited with Interest Equivalents as calculated under this Section 9(m) (such
Deferred Amount as increased by such Interest Equivalents being the
&#147;<I>Adjusted Deferred Amount</I>&#148;) and will thereafter be debited from the Cash Account and
credited to the Eligible Director&#146;s Current Stock Unit Account as of the date of
the next Annual Meeting following the date of such meeting (or, if the Eligible
Director&#146;s service on the Board terminates prior to the next Annual Meeting
following the date of such meeting, as of the first business day following his
or her Service Termination Date), with the number of Stock Units credited to the
Current Stock Unit Account being the amount obtained by dividing (i) the
relevant Adjusted Deferred Amount by (ii) the Fair Market Value of a share of
Stock on the date of such Annual Meeting or the Service Termination Date, as
applicable. As of the last day of each fiscal quarter and the Eligible
Director&#146;s Service Termination Date, the Eligible Director&#146;s Cash Account will
be credited with an Interest Equivalent equal to (i) the Rate of Interest,
multiplied by (ii) the Average Daily Cash Balance, multiplied by (iii) the
number of days during the fiscal quarter or other period during which such Cash
Account had a positive balance, divided by (iv) 365.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 10. Designation of
Beneficiaries</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>An Eligible Director may designate one or
more beneficiaries to receive any distributions under the Plan upon the Eligible
Director&#146;s death, and may change such designation at any time by submitting a
new beneficiary designation form to the Secretary.</FONT></P>

<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=1><FONT color=#b3b5b8>ANNEX

<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 11. Election to Receive
Stock</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(a) <u>Election</u>. An Eligible Director may
make a Stock Election to receive all or part of any or all of such Eligible
Director&#146;s Retainers in shares of Stock by submitting a Stock Election Form to
the Secretary indicating the Stock Amount. A Stock Election Form shall be
effective only with respect to Retainers payable after the date on which the
Secretary receives the Stock Election Form. Each Stock Election, once made,
shall be irrevocable. Notwithstanding the foregoing, a Stock Election may be
superseded with respect to future payments of an Eligible Director&#146;s Retainers
by submitting a new Stock Election Form to the Secretary.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(b) <u>Payment in Stock</u>. As of each Retainer
Payment Date, an Eligible Director who has made a Stock Election will receive,
in lieu of the Retainer elected to be received in Stock, a whole number of
shares of Stock (but not fractional shares) determined by dividing:</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(i) the amount of the Retainer that is
payable to the Eligible Director on the applicable Retainer Payment Date and is
subject to a Stock Election; by</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 30pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(ii) the Fair Market Value of a share of
Stock on such Retainer Payment Date.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>In no circumstances shall an Eligible
Director be entitled to receive, or shall the Company have any obligation to
issue to the Eligible Director, any fractional share of Stock. In lieu of any
fractional share of Stock, the Eligible Director shall be entitled to receive,
and the Company shall be obligated to pay to such Eligible Director, cash equal
to the value of any fractional share of Stock (determined by using the Fair
Market Value of a share of Stock on such Retainer Payment Date).</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 12. Fair Market
Value</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Fair
Market Value</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; shall mean, with respect to
each share of Stock for any day:</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(a) if the Stock is listed for trading on
the New York Stock Exchange, (i) the volume weighted average price of the Stock,
reflecting composite trading between 9:30 a.m. and 4:00 p.m. (Eastern time) on
such date, as reported by the Bloomberg Professional Service on the MS Equity
Volume at Price page under the &#147;VWAP&#148; field, at 4:00 p.m. on such date, rounded
up to the nearest whole cent, or, if not so reported, as reported by another
third party source to which the Company has access on such date, or if no such
reported sale of the Stock shall have occurred on such date, on the most recent
date on which such a reported sale occurred; or (ii) if the volume weighted
average price is not available from a third party source to which the Company
has access on such date or on the most recent date on which a reported sale
occurred, &#147;Fair Market Value&#148; will be the average of the high and low prices of
the Stock as reported on the Consolidated Transaction Reporting System on such
date, or if no such reported sale of the Stock shall have occurred on such date,
on the most recent date on which such a reported sale occurred; or</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(b) if the Stock is not so listed, but is
listed on another national securities exchange, the closing price, regular way,
of the Stock on such exchange, rounded up to the nearest whole cent, on which
the largest number of shares of Stock have been traded in the aggregate on the
preceding twenty trading days, or, if no such reported sale of the Stock shall
have occurred on such date on such exchange, on the most recent date on which
such a reported sale occurred on such exchange, or</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(c) if the Stock is not listed for trading
on a national securities exchange, the average of the closing bid and asked
prices as reported by the National Association of Securities Dealers, rounded up
to the nearest whole cent, or, if no such prices shall have been so reported for
such date, on the most recent date for which such prices were so
reported.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 13. Issuance of
Stock</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(a) <U>Restrictions on Transferability</U>. All
shares of Stock delivered under the Plan shall be subject to such stop-transfer
orders and other restrictions as the Company may deem advisable or legally
necessary under any laws, statutes, rules, regulations and other legal
requirements, including, without limitation, those of any stock exchange upon
which the Stock is then listed and any applicable federal, state or foreign
securities law.</FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=2><FONT color=#007bc4>B-8</FONT></FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <FONT face=Arial size=2><FONT color=#b3b5b8>Morgan Stanley 2017 Proxy Statement</FONT></FONT></P>

<DIV style="PAGE-BREAK-BEFORE: always"></DIV><BR>
<P align=justify><B><FONT face=Arial size=2><A HREF="#toc">Table of Contents</A></FONT></B></P>
<P align=right><FONT face=Arial size=1><FONT color=#b3b5b8>ANNEX
B</FONT></FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>(b) <u>Compliance with Laws</u>. Anything to the
contrary herein notwithstanding, the Company shall not be required to issue any
shares of Stock under the Plan if, in the opinion of legal counsel to the
Company, the issuance and delivery of such shares would constitute a violation
by the Eligible Director or the Company of any applicable law or regulation of
any governmental authority, including, without limitation, federal and state
securities laws, or the regulations of any stock exchanges on which the
Company&#146;s securities may then be listed.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 14. Withholding
Taxes</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Company may require as a condition of
delivery of any shares of Stock that the Eligible Director remit (i) in cash,
(ii) by tendering (or attesting to the ownership of) shares of Stock that the
Company determines will not result in unfavorable accounting treatment or (iii)
by the Company withholding shares of Stock, an amount sufficient to satisfy all
foreign, federal, state, local and other governmental withholding tax
requirements relating thereto (if any) and, exclusively in the case of an award
that does not constitute a deferral of compensation subject to Section 409A, any
or all indebtedness or other obligation of the Eligible Director to the Company
or any of its subsidiaries. In the case of any award that constitutes a deferral
of compensation subject to Section 409A, the Company may not withhold shares of
Stock to satisfy obligations that an Eligible Director owes to the Company or
any of its subsidiaries other than with respect to taxes or other governmental
charges imposed on amounts received by the Eligible Director pursuant to such
award, except to the extent such withholding is not prohibited by Section 409A
and would not cause the Eligible Director to recognize income for United States
federal income tax purposes prior to the time of payment of the award or to
incur interest or additional tax under Section 409A. Any shares tendered or
withheld pursuant to this Section 14 will be valued at Fair Market Value on the
relevant payment or exercise date, as applicable.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 15. Plan Amendments and
Termination</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Board may suspend or terminate the
Plan at any time, in whole or in part. Termination of the Plan shall not
adversely affect the rights of Eligible Directors in Career Stock Unit Accounts,
Cash Accounts and Current Stock Unit Accounts outstanding at the time of
termination. Notwithstanding any termination of the Plan, distributions to
Eligible Directors in respect of their Career Stock Unit Accounts, Cash Accounts
and Current Stock Unit Accounts shall be made at the times and in the manner
provided herein.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Board may also alter, amend or modify
the Plan at any time. These amendments may include (but are not limited to)
changes that the Board considers necessary or advisable as a result of changes
in, or the adoption or interpretation of, any law, regulation, ruling, judicial
decision or accounting standards (collectively, &#147;<I>Legal Requirements</I>&#148;). The Board may
not amend or modify the Plan in a manner that would materially impair an
Eligible Director&#146;s rights in any Career Stock Unit Account, Cash Account or
Current Stock Unit Account without the Eligible Director&#146;s consent;
<I>provided,</I> <I>however</I>, that the Board may, without an Eligible Director&#146;s consent, amend or
modify the Plan in any manner that it considers necessary or advisable to comply
with any Legal Requirement or to ensure that amounts credited to an Eligible
Director&#146;s Career Stock Unit Account, Cash Account or Current Stock Unit Account
are not subject to federal, state or local income tax prior to
payment.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>Notwithstanding the foregoing, if any  provision of this
Plan would, in the reasonable, good faith judgment of the  Company, result in or likely result in the imposition on any
Eligible Director  or any other person of any tax, interest or  penalty under Section 409A,
the Company may reform this Plan or any provision hereof, without the consent of any Eligible Director, in the manner that the Company reasonably and in
good  faith determines to be necessary or advisable to avoid the imposition of such  tax, interest or penalty; <I>provided</I>, <I>however</I>,
that any such reformation shall, to the maximum extent the  Company reasonably and in good faith determines to be possible,
retain the  economic and tax benefits to the Eligible Directors hereunder while not  materially increasing the cost to the
Company of providing such benefits to the  Eligible Directors.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Board may delegate to the Plan
Administrator its authority under this Section 15 to amend any provision of the
Plan for which approval by the Board (or a committee thereof) is not required
under applicable law or the rules of any national securities exchange on which
the Stock is traded.</FONT></P>

<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 16. Listing, Registration and
Legal Compliance</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>If the Plan Administrators shall at any
time determine that any Consent (as hereinafter defined) is necessary or
desirable as a condition of, or in connection with, the granting of any award
under the Plan, the issuance or purchase of shares or other rights hereunder or
the taking of any other action hereunder (each such action being hereinafter
referred to as a &#147;<I>Plan Action</I>&#148;), then such Plan Action shall not be taken, in whole or in
part, unless and until such Consent shall have been effected or obtained. The
term &#147;<I>Consent</I>&#148; as used herein with respect to any Plan Action means (i) the listing,
registrations or qualifications in respect thereof upon any securities exchange
or under any foreign, federal, state or local law, rule or regulation, (ii) any
and all consents, clearances and approvals in respect of a Plan Action by any governmental or other regulatory bodies, or (iii) any and all written agreements and representations by an Eligible Director with respect to the disposition of Stock or with respect to any other matter, which the Plan Administrators shall deem necessary or desirable in order to comply with the terms of any such listing, registration or qualification or to obtain an exemption from the requirement that any such listing, qualification or registration be made.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 17. Right
Reserved</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>Nothing in the Plan shall confer upon any
Eligible Director the right to continue as a director of the Company or affect
any right that the Company or any Eligible Director may have to terminate the
service of such Eligible Director.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 18. Rights as a
Stockholder</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>Except as otherwise provided by the terms
of any applicable Benefit Plan Trust, an Eligible Director shall not, by reason
of any stock option, Director Stock, Stock Unit or Stock Amount, have any rights
as a stockholder of the Company until Stock has been issued to such Eligible
Director.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 19. Unfunded
Plan</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Plan shall be unfunded and shall not
create (or be construed to create) a trust or a separate fund or funds. The Plan
shall not establish any fiduciary relationship between the Company and any
Eligible Director or other person. To the extent any person holds any rights by
virtue of a pending grant or deferral under the Plan, such rights shall be no
greater than the rights of an unsecured general creditor of the Company.
Notwithstanding the foregoing, the Company may (but shall not be obligated to)
contribute shares of Stock corresponding to Stock Units to a Benefit Plan Trust,
provided that the principal and income of any such Benefit Plan Trust shall be
subject to the claims of general creditors of the Company. The Company may amend
the terms of any Benefit Plan Trust as applicable to any one or more Eligible
Directors in order to procure favorable tax treatment for such Eligible
Director(s) or to comply with the laws applicable in any non-U.S.
jurisdiction.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 20. Governing
Law</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>The Plan is deemed adopted, made and
delivered in New York and shall be governed by the laws of the State of New York
applicable to agreements made and to be performed entirely within such
state.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 21. Severability</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>If any part of the Plan is declared by any
court or governmental authority to be unlawful or invalid, such unlawfulness or
invalidity shall not invalidate any portion of the Plan not declared to be
unlawful or invalid. Any Section or part of a Section so declared to be unlawful
or invalid shall, if possible, be construed in a manner that will give effect to
the terms of such Section or part of a Section to the fullest extent possible
while remaining lawful and valid.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 22. Notices</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>All notices and other communications
hereunder shall be given in writing and shall be deemed given when personally
delivered against receipt or five days after having been mailed by registered or
certified mail, postage prepaid, return receipt requested, addressed as follows:
(a) if to the Company: Morgan Stanley, 1585 Broadway, New York, New York 10036,
Attention: Corporate Secretary; and (b) if to an Eligible Director, at the
Eligible Director&#146;s principal residential address last furnished to the Company.
Either party may, by notice, change the address to which notice to such party is
to be given.</FONT></P>

<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 23. Section

for the purposes of convenience only and are not intended to define or limit the
contents of said Sections.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section 24. Definitions</FONT></B></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>As used in the Plan, the following terms
shall have the meanings indicated below:</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Account</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means Cash Account, Career
Stock Unit Account or Current Stock Unit Account, as applicable. </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Adjusted Deferred Amount</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; has the
meaning set forth in Section 9(m).</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Annual
Meeting</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means an annual meeting of the
Company&#146;s stockholders. </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Annual
Retainer</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means a cash retainer for services
as a member of the Board.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Annual
Service Period</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means the period from the
immediately preceding Annual Meeting until the next succeeding Annual
Meeting.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Annual
Stock Units</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means the Stock Units awarded to
an Eligible Director pursuant to Section 6(b).</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Average
Daily Cash Balance</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means the sum of the
daily balances for a Cash Account for any quarter or shorter period for which
the calculation is made, divided by the number of days on which a positive
balance existed in such Cash Account.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Awards</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means Initial Awards and
Subsequent Awards.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Benefit
Plan Trust</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means any trust established by
the Company under which Eligible Directors, or Eligible Directors and
participants in designated employee benefit plans of the Company, constitute the
principal beneficiaries.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Board</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means the board of directors of
the Company.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Career
Stock Unit Account</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means a bookkeeping
account to which Initial Stock Units and Annual Stock Units are credited
pursuant to Section 6(a) and Section 6(b).</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Career
Stock Units</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; has the meaning set forth in
Section 6(b).</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Cash
Account</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means a bookkeeping account to which
Meeting Fees are credited pursuant to Section 9(m) or which had a positive
balance as of the Stock Unit Transition Date.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Cause</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means, with respect to any
Eligible Director, termination of service on the Board on account of any act of
(A) fraud or intentional misrepresentation, or (B) embezzlement,
misappropriation or conversion of assets or opportunities of the Company or any
affiliate.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Committee Retainer</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means a cash
retainer for services as a member or chair of any committee of the Board.
</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Company</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; has the meaning set forth in
Section 1.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Consent</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; has the meaning set forth in
Section 16.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Current</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2></FONT> <I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Stock Unit Account</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means a
bookkeeping account to which Deferred Amounts are credited pursuant to Section
6(a), Section 6(b) or Section 9(b).</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Current</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2></FONT> <I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Stock Units</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means Annual Stock Units
and Initial Stock Units credited to the Eligible Director&#146;s Current Stock Unit
Account pursuant to Section 6(a) or Section 6(b).</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Deferral Election</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means a deferral
election by an Eligible Director made with respect to any Retainers, Director
Stock, Initial Stock Units and/or Annual Stock Units.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Deferral Election Form</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means an
election form submitted by an Eligible Director to the Secretary with respect to
any Retainers, Director Stock, or Stock Units.</FONT></P>

<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Deferred Amount</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means any amount, in
dollars, of Retainers, Initial Stock Units and/or Annual Stock Units that an
Eligible Director elects to defer, as indicated on the relevant Deferral
Election Form.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Director Stock</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means shares of Stock
awarded to an Eligible Director for service on the Board. As of the Stock Unit
Transition Date, no additional Director Stock will be awarded under the Plan,
but Director Stock remains one of the types of award that the stockholders of
the Company have authorized for the Plan, and nothing herein shall impair the
authority of the Board under Section 15 to amend the Plan in the future to
provide for awards of Director Stock without obtaining additional stockholder
approval.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Disability</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means a &#147;permanent and
total disability&#148; as defined in Section 22(e)(3) of the Internal Revenue Code of
1986, as amended.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Distribution Commencement Date</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means
the date that an Eligible Director elects as the date on which distribution of
Deferred Amounts should begin, as indicated on the relevant Deferral Election
Form.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Dividend Equivalents</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; has the meaning
set forth in Section 9(i).</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Elective Stock Units</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means Stock
Units that an Eligible Director elects to receive in lieu of Retainers pursuant
to Section 9(a).</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Eligible Directors</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; has the meaning
set forth in Section 2. </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt">
<I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;Fair Market
Value</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; has the meaning set forth in Section
12.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Governmental Employer</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; has the meaning
set forth in Section 8(b).</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Governmental Service Resignation</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; has
the meaning set forth in Section 8(b).</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Initial
Awards</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means any awards made to an Eligible
Director pursuant to Section 6(a), including any predecessor version
thereof.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Initial
Stock Units</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means the Stock Units awarded to
an Eligible Director pursuant to Section 6(a).</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Interest Equivalent</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means an
additional amount to be credited to a Cash Account calculated in accordance with
Section 9(m).</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Lead
Director Retainer</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means a cash retainer for
services as the lead director of the Board.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Meeting
Fees</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means fees (if any) payable to an
Eligible Director for participation in meetings of the Board or any committee
thereof.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Normal
Retirement</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means the termination of service
on the Board for retirement at or after attaining age 65, other than for Cause,
Disability or death.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Plan</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; has the meaning set forth in
Section 1.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Rate of
Interest</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means the time weighted average
interest rate paid by the Company for a quarter, or such shorter period from the
end of the preceding quarter to an Eligible Director&#146;s Service Termination Date,
to institutions from which it borrows funds.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Retainer</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means the Annual Retainer,
the Committee Retainer and/or the Lead Director Retainer, as
applicable.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Retainer Payment Date</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means, with
respect to any Retainer, the date as of which an Eligible Director becomes
entitled to payment of Retainer.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Section
409A</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means Section 409A of the Internal
Revenue Code of 1986, as amended, and the rules, regulations and guidance
thereunder (or any successor provisions thereto).</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Service
Termination Date</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means the date of an
Eligible Director&#146;s termination of service on the Board or such later date as
constitutes the Eligible Director&#146;s separation from service with the Company for
purposes of Section 409A.</FONT></P>

<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Stock</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means the Company&#146;s common
stock, par value $0.01 per share, and any other shares into which such stock
shall thereafter be changed by reason of any merger, reorganization,
recapitalization, consolidation, split-up, combination of shares or similar
event as set forth in and in accordance with Section 4.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Stock
Amount</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means the percentage of the Retainers
that an Eligible Director elects to have paid in Stock, as indicated on the
relevant Stock Election Form.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Stock
Election</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means an election by an Eligible
Director to receive all or a portion of the Eligible Director&#146;s Retainers in
shares of Stock.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Stock
Election Form</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means the election form
submitted by an Eligible Director to the Secretary as provided in Section
11(a).</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Stock
Option Transition Date</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; has the meaning set
forth in Section 5(a). </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Stock Unit Transition
Date</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means November 16, 2009.</FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;</FONT><I><FONT face=Arial size=2>Stock
Units</FONT></I><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#148; means Initial Stock Units, Annual
Stock Units and/or Elective Stock Units, as applicable. </FONT></P>
<P ALIGN="LEFT" STYLE="text-indent: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&#147;<I>Subsequent Awards</I>&#148; means
any awards made to an Eligible Director pursuant to Section 6(b), including any
predecessor version thereof.</FONT></P>
<P align=right><FONT face=Arial size=2><FONT color=#b3b5b8>Morgan Stanley 2017
Proxy Statement</FONT></FONT><FONT face=Arial size=2></FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <FONT face=Arial size=2><FONT color=#007bc4>B-13</FONT></FONT></P>
<HR align=center width="100%" noShade SIZE=2>
