<P align=left><FONT face=Arial size=7><FONT style="font-size: 36pt" color=#007bc4>Our Core
Values</FONT></FONT></P>
<P align=left><FONT style="font-size: 16pt" face=Arial>Since our founding in 1935, Morgan Stanley
has consistently delivered first-class business in a first-class way.
Underpinning all that we do are four core values.</FONT></P>
<TABLE style="BORDER-COLLAPSE: collapse" cellSpacing=0 cellPadding=0 width="100%" border=0>

  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left; width: 54%; padding-right: 15pt"><FONT color=#007bc4><FONT style="font-size: 16pt" face=Arial size=5>PUTTING CLIENTS FIRST</FONT></FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top align=left width="45%"><FONT color=#007bc4><FONT style="font-size: 16pt" face=Arial size=5>DOING
      THE RIGHT THING</FONT></FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left; width: 54%; padding-right: 15pt">&nbsp;</TD>
    <TD vAlign=top align=left width="45%"></TD></TR>
  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left; width: 54%; padding-right: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial style="font-size: 11pt">Always keep the client&#146;s
      interest first.<BR>&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top align=left width="45%"><FONT face=Arial style="font-size: 11pt">Act with
    integrity.</FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left; width: 54%; padding-right: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial style="font-size: 11pt">Working with colleagues to
      deliver the best of the Firm to every client.</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top align=left width="45%"><FONT face=Arial style="font-size: 11pt">Think like an owner to
      create long-term shareholder value.</FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left; width: 54%; padding-right: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top align=left width="45%"><FONT face=Arial size=2></FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left; width: 54%; padding-right: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial style="font-size: 11pt">Listen to what the client
      is saying and needs.</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top align=left width="45%"><FONT face=Arial style="font-size: 11pt">Value and reward honesty,
      collegiality and character.</FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%" colSpan=2>&nbsp;</TD></TR>
  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left; width: 54%; padding-right: 15pt"><FONT color=#007bc4><FONT style="font-size: 16pt" face=Arial size=5>LEADING WITH EXCEPTIONAL IDEAS</FONT></FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top align=left width="45%"><FONT color=#007bc4><FONT style="font-size: 16pt" face=Arial size=5>GIVING
      BACK</FONT></FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left; width: 54%; padding-right: 15pt"></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top align=left width="45%">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left; width: 54%; padding-right: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial style="font-size: 11pt">Win by breaking new
      ground.</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top align=left width="45%"><FONT face=Arial style="font-size: 11pt">Be generous with your
      expertise, your time and your money.</FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left; width: 54%; padding-right: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top align=left width="45%"><FONT face=Arial size=2></FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left; width: 54%; padding-right: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial style="font-size: 11pt">Let the facts and
      different points of view broaden your perspective.</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top align=left width="45%"><FONT face=Arial style="font-size: 11pt">Invest in the future of
      our communities and our Firm.</FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left; width: 54%; padding-right: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial size=2>&nbsp;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top align=left width="45%"><FONT face=Arial size=2></FONT></TD></TR>
  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: left; width: 54%; padding-right: 15pt"><FONT face=Arial style="font-size: 11pt">Be vigilant about what we can do better.</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top align=left width="45%"><FONT face=Arial style="font-size: 11pt">Mentor our next
      generation.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><BR>

and our history are rooted in serving our clients.&#148;</FONT></FONT></P>

      <P align=justify><FONT face=Arial size=1>Sign exactly as imprinted (do not
      print). If shares are held jointly, EACH holder should sign. Executors,
      administrators, trustees, guardians and others signing in a representative
      capacity should indicate the capacity in which they sign. An authorized
      officer signing on behalf of a corporation should indicate the name of the
      corporation and the officer&#146;s title.</FONT></P></TD></TR>

instruction forms that you may receive. </FONT></P>
<P align=center><B><FONT face=Arial size=1>PLEASE SUBMIT YOUR PROXY BY PHONE OR
BY INTERNET,<BR></FONT></B><B><FONT face=Arial size=1>OR RETURN THIS PROXY CARD
AFTER SIGNING AND DATING IT ON THE REVERSE
SIDE.</FONT></B></P>
<P align=center><B><FONT face=Arial size=1>THIS PROXY WILL BE VOTED AS DIRECTED.
IF THIS PROXY IS SIGNED, BUT NO DIRECTION IS MADE, IT WILL BE VOTED
IN<BR>ACCORDANCE WITH THE RECOMMENDATION OF MORGAN STANLEY&#146;S BOARD OF
DIRECTORS.</FONT></B></P>

  <TR vAlign=bottom>
    <TD style="BORDER-TOP: #000000 1pt dashed" vAlign=middle noWrap align=center width="95%"><B><FONT face=Arial size=1>&nbsp;</FONT></B></TD>
    <TD style="BORDER-TOP: #000000 1pt dashed" vAlign=middle noWrap align=right width="5%">
      <P align=right><FONT face=Arial size=1>E19167-P87539-Z69477</FONT></P></TD></TR></TABLE>
<DIV style="BORDER-RIGHT: black 2pt solid; PADDING-RIGHT: 10pt; BORDER-TOP: black 2pt solid; PADDING-LEFT: 10pt; PADDING-BOTTOM: 2pt; BORDER-LEFT: black 2pt solid; PADDING-TOP: 2pt; BORDER-BOTTOM: black 2pt solid">
<P align=center><B><FONT face=Arial>MORGAN
STANLEY</FONT></B></P>
<P align=center><B><FONT face=Arial size=2>THIS PROXY IS SOLICITED ON BEHALF OF
THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS<BR>FOR THE 2017 ANNUAL MEETING OF SHAREHOLDERS, MAY 22,
2017</FONT></B></P>
<P align=justify><FONT face=Arial size=1>The undersigned hereby appoints Eric F.
Grossman and Martin M. Cohen, and each of them, attorneys and proxies, with full
power of substitution, to represent and to vote on behalf of the undersigned all
of the shares of common stock of Morgan Stanley that the undersigned is entitled
in any capacity to vote if personally present at the 2017 Annual Meeting of
Shareholders to be held on May 22, 2017, and at any adjournments or
postponements thereof, in accordance with the instructions set forth on the
reverse side of this proxy card and with the same effect as though the
undersigned were present in person and voting such shares. Each of the proxies
is authorized in his discretion to vote for the election of another person to
the Board of Directors if any nominee named herein becomes unable to serve or
for good cause will not serve, upon all matters incident to the conduct of the
meeting, and upon such other business as may properly come before the
meeting.</FONT></P>
<P align=justify><B><FONT face=Arial size=1>BENEFIT PLAN
PARTICIPANTS</FONT></B></P>
<P align=justify><FONT face=Arial size=1>I hereby direct the following to vote,
in person or by proxy, all of the shares of Morgan Stanley common stock held for
my benefit in Morgan Stanley benefit plans at the</FONT><B><FONT face=Arial size=1> </FONT></B><FONT face=Arial size=1>2017 Annual Meeting of Shareholders
to be held on May 22, 2017, and at any and all adjournments or postponements
thereof, as indicated on the reverse side of this voting instruction form, and,
in its (or the proxies&#146;) discretion, for the election of another person to the
Board of Directors if any nominee named herein becomes unable to serve or for
good cause will not serve, upon all matters incident to the conduct of the
meeting, and upon such other business as may properly come before the
meeting.</FONT></P>

  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 7pt">&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=justify><FONT face=Arial size=1>The Northern Trust Company
      (Northern Trust), as trustee under the Morgan Stanley 401(k) Plan (the
      "Plan"). </FONT><B><FONT face=Arial size=1>As a participant in and a named
      fiduciary under the Plan, I understand that (A) if I sign, date, and
      return this form, Northern Trust will vote or grant proxies in accordance
      with the Board of Directors&#146; recommendation as to each proposal for which
      I do not give voting instructions, (B) Northern Trust will vote or grant
      proxies for all undirected (other than pursuant to clause (A)) and/or
      forfeited shares, as applicable, in the same respective proportion as the
      shares of all participants who have timely delivered properly executed
      voting instructions, unless to do so would be inconsistent with Northern
      Trust&#146;s duties, and (C) Northern Trust will hold my voting instructions in
      confidence to the extent required by applicable law or regulations or the
      governing instrument.<BR>&nbsp;</FONT></B></P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 7pt">&#9679;</FONT></TD>
    <TD vAlign=top width="99%">
      <P align=justify><FONT face=Arial size=1>State Street Bank and Trust Company,
as trustee under a trust agreement (Trust), in connection with the Equity
Incentive Compensation Plan, the 2009 Replacement Equity Incentive Compensation
Plan for Morgan Stanley Smith Barney Employees, the Employees&#146; Equity
Accumulation Plan, the Tax Deferred Equity Participation Plan and the 1995
Equity Incentive Compensation Plan. </FONT><B><FONT face=Arial size=1>I
understand that, subject to the Trust&#146;s terms, (A) if I sign, date and return
this form, State Street will vote in accordance with the Board of Directors&#146;
recommendation as to each proposal for which I do not give voting instructions,
(B) State Street will vote with respect to all shares held in the Trust in
connection with these plans for which no proper instructions are received (other
than pursuant to clause (A)) in the same proportion as the shares held in
connection with these plans for which it has received proper instructions, and
(C) State Street will vote in its discretion, after due consideration, on all
other matters that may properly come before the meeting.</FONT></B><BR>&nbsp;</P></TD></TR>
  <TR>
    <TD style="PADDING-RIGHT: 8pt" vAlign=top width="1%"><FONT style="FONT-SIZE: 7pt">&#9679;</FONT></TD>

      understand that, subject to the Trust&#146;s terms, (A) if I do not sign, date
      and return this form, State Street will not vote or grant proxies with
      respect to these shares, and (B) if I sign, date and return this form,
      State Street will vote (i) in accordance with the Board of Directors&#146;

      other matters that may properly come before the
      meeting.<BR>&nbsp;</FONT></B></P></TD></TR>
